1
00:04:43,659 --> 00:04:45,035
Get in there now!

2
00:04:45,202 --> 00:04:46,996
Get in! Get in!

3
00:04:47,163 --> 00:04:49,123
Get in there, Dude!

4
00:04:49,500 --> 00:04:50,958
Get in now!

5
00:04:51,284 --> 00:04:52,746
Come on!

6
00:04:54,545 --> 00:04:57,298
All right!

7
00:05:11,437 --> 00:05:13,689
Got room for one more?

8
00:05:13,856 --> 00:05:16,191
Who the hell are you?!

9
00:05:16,359 --> 00:05:18,069
And what happened to them?

10
00:05:20,446 --> 00:05:23,490
Name's Major Marquis Warren,
former U.S. Cavalry.

11
00:05:23,658 --> 00:05:27,912
Currently a servant of the court.
Trying to bring a couple no-goods into market.

12
00:05:28,079 --> 00:05:30,039
Got the paperwork on 'em in my pocket.

13
00:05:30,206 --> 00:05:32,291
You takin' 'em into Red Rock?

14
00:05:32,458 --> 00:05:35,628
- Figure that's where you headed, right?
- I am.

15
00:05:35,795 --> 00:05:39,550
That damn blasted blizzard
has been on our ass for the last three hours.

16
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:45,022
There ain't no way we gonna make it
all the way to Red Rock 'fore it catches us.

17
00:05:45,189 --> 00:05:47,389
So you hightailin' it halfway,
to Minnie's Haberdashery?

18
00:05:47,556 --> 00:05:49,516
You know I am.

19
00:05:49,684 --> 00:05:53,020
- May I come aboard?
- Well, smoke,

20
00:05:53,187 --> 00:05:56,190
if it up to me, yes.

21
00:05:56,357 --> 00:05:58,275
But it ain't up to me.

22
00:05:58,442 --> 00:06:00,027
Who's it up to?

23
00:06:00,194 --> 00:06:01,862
Fella in the wagon.

24
00:06:02,029 --> 00:06:04,406
Fella in the wagon
ain't partial to company?

25
00:06:04,573 --> 00:06:08,410
Fella in the wagon, he paid for a private trip,
and I'm here to tell you,

26
00:06:08,577 --> 00:06:10,371
he paid a pretty penny for privacy.

27
00:06:10,538 --> 00:06:13,290
So if you want to go to Minnie's with us,

28
00:06:13,457 --> 00:06:15,626
you gonna have to talk to him.

29
00:06:15,793 --> 00:06:18,212
Well...

30
00:06:18,379 --> 00:06:20,673
that's what I'll do.

31
00:06:22,216 --> 00:06:25,219
Hold it, black fella.

32
00:06:25,386 --> 00:06:28,681
'Fore you approach,
you take them two guns of yours

33
00:06:28,848 --> 00:06:32,059
and you lay 'em on that rock
over yonder.

34
00:06:32,226 --> 00:06:36,647
Then you raise both your hands
way above your hat.

35
00:06:36,814 --> 00:06:38,941
Then you approach.

36
00:06:39,108 --> 00:06:40,526
Molasses-like.

37
00:06:41,652 --> 00:06:43,696
Real trustin' fella?

38
00:06:43,863 --> 00:06:45,698
Not so much.

39
00:06:58,169 --> 00:07:00,212
Put 'em down.

40
00:07:08,846 --> 00:07:10,681
Come on ahead.

41
00:07:10,848 --> 00:07:14,226
I said way above your hat,
goddamn it!

42
00:07:15,603 --> 00:07:18,230
Now come forward.

43
00:07:18,397 --> 00:07:20,191
That's far enough.

44
00:07:26,155 --> 00:07:28,031
Well, I'll be dogged.

45
00:07:28,199 --> 00:07:29,950
You a black fella I know.

46
00:07:30,117 --> 00:07:32,369
Colonel somethin'-or-other Warren, right?

47
00:07:32,536 --> 00:07:35,414
Major Marquis Warren.

48
00:07:35,581 --> 00:07:37,291
I know you, too.

49
00:07:37,458 --> 00:07:39,376
We shared a steak dinner

50
00:07:39,543 --> 00:07:41,462
once upon a time in Chattanooga.

51
00:07:41,629 --> 00:07:43,380
You John Ruth The Hangman.

52
00:07:43,547 --> 00:07:44,965
That'd be me.

53
00:07:45,132 --> 00:07:47,801
- How long's that been?
- Since that steak?

54
00:07:49,438 --> 00:07:51,054
Eight months.

55
00:07:51,222 --> 00:07:53,640
So why don't you explain to me

56
00:07:53,808 --> 00:07:55,851
what a African bounty hunter's doin'

57
00:07:56,018 --> 00:07:59,146
wanderin' around in the snow
in the middle of Wyoming?

58
00:07:59,313 --> 00:08:01,190
Trying to get a couple of bounties
in to Red Rock.

59
00:08:01,357 --> 00:08:04,068
- So you still in business?
- You know I am.

60
00:08:04,235 --> 00:08:05,986
Happened to your horse?

61
00:08:06,153 --> 00:08:09,364
Circumstances caused us
to have to take the long way round.

62
00:08:09,532 --> 00:08:11,408
My horse couldn't make it.

63
00:08:11,575 --> 00:08:13,952
You don't know nothin'
'bout this filly here.

64
00:08:14,119 --> 00:08:15,496
Nope.

65
00:08:15,663 --> 00:08:17,873
- Don't even know her name?
- Nope.

66
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:21,710
Well, I guess that makes this
one fortuitous wagon.

67
00:08:21,877 --> 00:08:23,754
I sure as hell hope so.

68
00:08:23,921 --> 00:08:27,508
Major Marquis Warren,
this here's Daisy Domergue.

69
00:08:29,009 --> 00:08:31,845
Domergue, to you this is Major Warren.

70
00:08:32,012 --> 00:08:33,514
Howdy, nigger.

71
00:08:35,182 --> 00:08:36,975
She's a pepper, ain't she?

72
00:08:37,142 --> 00:08:40,229
Now, girl, don't you know the darkies
don't like being called niggers no more?

73
00:08:40,396 --> 00:08:43,232
- They find it offensive.
- I been called worse.

74
00:08:43,399 --> 00:08:46,235
Now, that I can believe.
You never heard of her?

75
00:08:46,402 --> 00:08:47,694
Should I?

76
00:08:47,862 --> 00:08:51,365
Well, she ain't no John Wilkes Booth,
but maybe you might heard tell

77
00:08:51,532 --> 00:08:53,325
about the price on her head.

78
00:08:53,492 --> 00:08:55,202
- How much?
- $10,000.

79
00:08:55,369 --> 00:08:56,912
Damn.

80
00:08:57,079 --> 00:08:59,373
What'd she do, kill Lily Langtry?

81
00:08:59,540 --> 00:09:01,083
Not quite.

82
00:09:01,250 --> 00:09:04,086
That ten thousand's
practically in my pocket.

83
00:09:04,253 --> 00:09:07,589
It's why I ain't too anxious
to be handin' out rides,

84
00:09:07,756 --> 00:09:10,133
especially to professionals
open for business.

85
00:09:10,301 --> 00:09:14,722
I can certainly appreciate that.
But I ain't got no designs on her.

86
00:09:14,889 --> 00:09:17,474
One of my fellas over there
is worth $4,000,

87
00:09:17,641 --> 00:09:20,644
another one's worth $3,000,
and one of 'em's worth $1,000.

88
00:09:20,811 --> 00:09:23,144
That's damn sure good enough for me.

89
00:09:23,375 --> 00:09:29,778
Well... let me see their paperwork.
Like I said, molasses-like.

90
00:09:38,537 --> 00:09:39,958
Back off.

91
00:10:08,609 --> 00:10:10,611
Look, I sure hate to interrupt you all,

92
00:10:10,778 --> 00:10:14,364
but we got a cold damn blizzard
that's hot on our ass

93
00:10:14,531 --> 00:10:16,283
that we're tryin' to beat to shelter!

94
00:10:16,450 --> 00:10:21,580
I realize that! Now, shut your mouth
and hold them damn horses while I think!

95
00:10:24,249 --> 00:10:26,668
Okay, boy, we'll give it a try.

96
00:10:26,835 --> 00:10:30,047
But you leave them two pistols
over yonder with the driver.

97
00:10:33,050 --> 00:10:36,846
Hey, you ain't really gonna let that nigger
ride in here, is ya?

98
00:10:37,012 --> 00:10:39,145
I mean, maybe up there with O.B., but...

99
00:10:40,557 --> 00:10:42,809
How ya like
the sound of them bells, bitch?

100
00:10:42,977 --> 00:10:44,647
They real pretty, ain't they?

101
00:10:45,854 --> 00:10:49,567
You open up your trashy mouth again,
I'll knock out them front teeth for ya.

102
00:10:49,733 --> 00:10:51,693
You got it?

103
00:10:51,860 --> 00:10:53,570
Yeah.

104
00:10:53,737 --> 00:10:55,864
Let me hear ya say, "I got it."

105
00:10:57,783 --> 00:11:00,369
I got it.

106
00:11:00,536 --> 00:11:03,747
I'm gonna need a hand
tyin' these fellas up on the roof.

107
00:11:03,914 --> 00:11:07,634
Give O.B. $50 when we get to Red Rock.
He'll help ya.

108
00:11:07,801 --> 00:11:10,921
Well, I agree with O.B.
This storm got me concerned.

109
00:11:11,088 --> 00:11:13,215
We get goin' a lot quicker
you helped out, too.

110
00:11:13,382 --> 00:11:16,259
Goddamn it to hell,
I'm already regrettin' this.

111
00:11:16,427 --> 00:11:20,848
Now, I can't likely help you tie fellas
to the roof with my wrist cuffed to hers.

112
00:11:21,015 --> 00:11:24,894
And my wrist is gonna stay cuffed to hers,
and she ain't never gonna leave my goddamn side

113
00:11:25,060 --> 00:11:27,854
till I personally put her
in the Red Rock jail!

114
00:11:28,022 --> 00:11:29,606
Now, do you got that?!

115
00:11:29,773 --> 00:11:31,358
Yeah, I got it.

116
00:11:31,525 --> 00:11:32,985
Good.

117
00:11:35,571 --> 00:11:37,155
Get in, Dude!

118
00:11:37,322 --> 00:11:38,699
Hut! Get in!

119
00:11:38,866 --> 00:11:41,576
Go on! Hut!

120
00:11:41,744 --> 00:11:43,036
Come on!

121
00:11:43,203 --> 00:11:46,790
Dude, Coconut, giddyup.

122
00:12:14,860 --> 00:12:17,237
Hut!

123
00:12:21,825 --> 00:12:23,952
Giddyup!

124
00:12:25,245 --> 00:12:27,581
Cimarron! Leche! Get in!

125
00:12:27,748 --> 00:12:29,666
So, what happened to your horse?

126
00:12:29,833 --> 00:12:31,293
Get in!

127
00:12:31,460 --> 00:12:33,170
He was kinda old.

128
00:12:33,337 --> 00:12:35,964
I done had him for a bit.

129
00:12:36,131 --> 00:12:38,133
When the weather
took a turn for the worse,

130
00:12:38,300 --> 00:12:41,261
well, he done what he could,
but he couldn't make it.

131
00:12:41,428 --> 00:12:43,680
- Get in!
- That's too bad.

132
00:12:43,847 --> 00:12:46,016
Yeah, it is.

133
00:12:46,183 --> 00:12:49,186
Me and ol' Lash done rode
a lot of miles together.

134
00:12:49,353 --> 00:12:51,229
Could say he was my best friend,

135
00:12:51,396 --> 00:12:55,442
if I considered stupid animals friends,
which I don't.

136
00:12:55,609 --> 00:12:58,070
Nevertheless, I'm gonna miss him.

137
00:12:59,696 --> 00:13:01,698
Leche!

138
00:13:01,865 --> 00:13:03,992
Who's this Daisy Domergue?

139
00:13:04,159 --> 00:13:06,787
A no damn good murdering bitch,
that's who.

140
00:13:06,954 --> 00:13:08,497
Come on, boys! Get up!

141
00:13:08,664 --> 00:13:11,709
I see you ain't got mixed emotions
about bringing a woman to a rope.

142
00:13:11,875 --> 00:13:14,669
By "woman," you mean her?

143
00:13:14,837 --> 00:13:17,297
No, I do not have mixed emotions.

144
00:13:17,464 --> 00:13:18,715
Get in!

145
00:13:18,882 --> 00:13:22,344
- So you taking her into Red Rock to hang.
- You bet.

146
00:13:22,511 --> 00:13:25,306
- You gonna wait round to watch it?
- You know I am.

147
00:13:25,472 --> 00:13:27,557
- Come on!
- I want to hear her neck snap

148
00:13:27,724 --> 00:13:29,017
with my own two ears.

149
00:13:29,184 --> 00:13:30,852
Get up, boys!

150
00:13:31,019 --> 00:13:33,396
- You never wait to watch 'em hang?
- Get up!

151
00:13:33,564 --> 00:13:35,482
My bounties never hang,

152
00:13:35,649 --> 00:13:37,859
'cause I never bring 'em in alive.

153
00:13:38,026 --> 00:13:40,278
- Never?
- Never ever.

154
00:13:40,445 --> 00:13:42,872
- Get up!
- We talked about this in Chattanooga.

155
00:13:43,039 --> 00:13:45,993
Bringing desperate men in alive's
a good way to get yourself dead.

156
00:13:46,160 --> 00:13:47,994
- Get in there!
- Can't catch me sleeping

157
00:13:48,162 --> 00:13:49,412
if I don't close my eyes.

158
00:13:49,580 --> 00:13:52,875
- I don't want to work that hard.
- No one said the job is supposed to be easy.

159
00:13:53,041 --> 00:13:55,043
No one said
it's supposed to be that hard, neither.

160
00:13:55,210 --> 00:13:58,046
- Get up, boys!
- But that, little lady,

161
00:13:58,213 --> 00:14:00,048
is why they call him "The Hangman."

162
00:14:00,215 --> 00:14:02,717
When the handbill says "dead or alive,"

163
00:14:02,885 --> 00:14:06,347
the rest of us shoot ya in the back
from up on top of a perch somewhere,

164
00:14:06,513 --> 00:14:08,223
- bring ya in dead over a saddle.
- Get in!

165
00:14:08,390 --> 00:14:12,018
But when John Ruth The Hangman
catches ya,

166
00:14:12,186 --> 00:14:14,440
you don't die from no bullet in the back.

167
00:14:16,023 --> 00:14:18,775
When The Hangman catches you,
you hang.

168
00:14:21,945 --> 00:14:24,030
You overrate him, nigger.

169
00:14:24,198 --> 00:14:27,784
I give ya he got guts,
but in the brains department,

170
00:14:27,951 --> 00:14:31,747
he like a man
who took a high dive in a low well.

171
00:14:35,542 --> 00:14:37,377
Now, Daisy,

172
00:14:37,544 --> 00:14:41,214
I want us to work out
a signal system of communication.

173
00:14:41,381 --> 00:14:46,595
When I elbow you real hard in the face,
that means "shut up."

174
00:14:46,762 --> 00:14:48,180
You got it?

175
00:14:49,389 --> 00:14:51,057
I got it.

176
00:14:51,225 --> 00:14:55,020
Get in there!

177
00:14:57,940 --> 00:15:00,067
Come on now, boys, get in!

178
00:15:08,116 --> 00:15:11,828
<i>Hey, little apple blossom</i>

179
00:15:11,995 --> 00:15:16,750
<i>What seems to be the problem?</i>

180
00:15:16,917 --> 00:15:20,170
<i>All the ones you tell your troubles to</i>

181
00:15:20,337 --> 00:15:24,341
<i>They don't really care for you</i>

182
00:15:24,508 --> 00:15:27,636
<i>Come and tell me what you're thinking</i>

183
00:15:27,803 --> 00:15:32,224
<i>'Cause just when the boat is sinking</i>

184
00:15:32,391 --> 00:15:35,644
<i>A little light is blinking</i>

185
00:15:35,811 --> 00:15:39,773
<i>And I will come and rescue you</i>

186
00:15:39,940 --> 00:15:43,526
<i>Lots of girls walk around in tears</i>

187
00:15:43,694 --> 00:15:47,280
<i>But that's not for you</i>

188
00:15:47,447 --> 00:15:50,116
<i>You've been looking all around for years</i>

189
00:15:50,284 --> 00:15:54,329
<i>For someone to tell your troubles to</i>

190
00:15:54,496 --> 00:15:58,333
<i>Come and sit with me and talk a while</i>

191
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:02,295
<i>Let me see your pretty little smile</i>

192
00:16:02,462 --> 00:16:05,382
<i>Put your troubles in a little pile</i>

193
00:16:05,549 --> 00:16:09,177
<i>And I will sort them out for you, all right.</i>

194
00:16:14,474 --> 00:16:15,854
Get in!

195
00:16:20,314 --> 00:16:21,774
Get in there!

196
00:16:29,489 --> 00:16:31,199
Giddyup!

197
00:16:33,910 --> 00:16:37,664
I... I know we only met each other
the once before,

198
00:16:37,831 --> 00:16:41,251
- and I don't mean to unduly imply intimacy,
- Get up!

199
00:16:41,418 --> 00:16:45,088
But, well...

200
00:16:45,255 --> 00:16:47,215
You still got it?

201
00:16:47,382 --> 00:16:50,094
- Do I still got what?
- Get in, now!

202
00:16:50,260 --> 00:16:52,345
The Lincoln letter.

203
00:16:52,512 --> 00:16:54,097
Course.

204
00:16:54,264 --> 00:16:56,516
Get up, boys!

205
00:16:56,683 --> 00:16:58,184
Got it on ya?

206
00:16:58,352 --> 00:17:00,271
- Come on!
- Where?

207
00:17:00,437 --> 00:17:02,105
Right here.

208
00:17:02,272 --> 00:17:03,857
Come on, boys! Get up!

209
00:17:04,024 --> 00:17:06,192
Look, I know you got to be
real careful with it and all,

210
00:17:06,360 --> 00:17:09,029
and I can imagine
you probably don't like taking it

211
00:17:09,196 --> 00:17:11,619
in and out of the envelope
all that often, but...

212
00:17:11,786 --> 00:17:12,991
Get up!

213
00:17:13,158 --> 00:17:16,995
If you wouldn't mind,
I'd sure appreciate seeing that again.

214
00:17:17,162 --> 00:17:18,580
Get in, boys!

215
00:17:18,747 --> 00:17:21,833
Giddyup!

216
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:23,209
You're right.

217
00:17:23,377 --> 00:17:25,462
I don't like taking it in and out

218
00:17:25,629 --> 00:17:27,714
- of the envelope that much.
- I... Yeah.

219
00:17:27,881 --> 00:17:29,215
- But...
- Get in!

220
00:17:29,383 --> 00:17:32,218
Seeing's how you saved my life and all...

221
00:17:32,386 --> 00:17:34,429
I suppose I could let you read it again.

222
00:17:34,596 --> 00:17:36,598
Get in!

223
00:17:36,765 --> 00:17:39,267
Get in there!

224
00:17:41,478 --> 00:17:43,438
Get up now!

225
00:17:49,319 --> 00:17:50,737
Get in!

226
00:17:50,904 --> 00:17:52,280
Giddyup!

227
00:17:58,537 --> 00:18:00,664
Get in, now!

228
00:18:04,918 --> 00:18:06,628
Get in!

229
00:18:17,472 --> 00:18:21,435
"Ole Mary Todd's calling,
so I guess it must be time for bed."

230
00:18:23,478 --> 00:18:25,355
Ole Mary Todd.

231
00:18:28,066 --> 00:18:30,276
Get in!

232
00:18:30,444 --> 00:18:32,654
- Well, that...
- Get up, boys!

233
00:18:32,821 --> 00:18:34,285
That gets me.

234
00:18:35,073 --> 00:18:36,991
Yeah, it gets me, too.

235
00:18:37,159 --> 00:18:38,952
Get in! Get in!

236
00:18:39,119 --> 00:18:42,122
You know what this is, tramp?

237
00:18:42,289 --> 00:18:44,499
It's a letter from Lincoln.

238
00:18:44,666 --> 00:18:47,085
- Letter from Lincoln to him.
- Get in there!

239
00:18:47,252 --> 00:18:48,503
Yeah.

240
00:18:48,670 --> 00:18:52,091
They shared a correspondence
during the war. They was pen pals.

241
00:18:52,257 --> 00:18:55,093
- And this is just one of the letters.
- Get up!

242
00:18:57,804 --> 00:18:59,514
What the...

243
00:18:59,681 --> 00:19:01,683
O.B.!

244
00:19:01,850 --> 00:19:03,227
Stop!

245
00:19:04,352 --> 00:19:05,731
Easy.

246
00:19:10,734 --> 00:19:13,069
All the stupid...

247
00:19:13,236 --> 00:19:15,697
Like to rip my goddamn arm off!

248
00:19:49,189 --> 00:19:52,775
I didn't drag her stinking ass
up this goddamn mountain

249
00:19:52,943 --> 00:19:55,195
just for you to break her neck
on the outskirts of town!

250
00:19:55,362 --> 00:19:57,906
You the one handed her
my goddamn letter!

251
00:19:58,073 --> 00:20:01,660
I didn't give it to her, I give it to you!

252
00:20:03,912 --> 00:20:05,997
That nigger like to bust my jaw.

253
00:20:09,042 --> 00:20:12,546
You ruin that letter of his,
that nigger gonna stomp your ass to death.

254
00:20:12,712 --> 00:20:15,882
And when he do,
I'm gonna sit back on that wagon wheel,

255
00:20:16,049 --> 00:20:17,553
watch and laugh!

256
00:20:18,343 --> 00:20:20,053
How is it?

257
00:20:20,220 --> 00:20:22,013
Well, she ain't help it none.

258
00:20:22,180 --> 00:20:23,973
But it's all right.

259
00:20:24,140 --> 00:20:27,810
Is that the way
niggers treat their ladies?

260
00:20:27,978 --> 00:20:30,438
You ain't no goddamn lady!

261
00:20:37,571 --> 00:20:38,988
Hey, Mr. Ruth!

262
00:20:39,155 --> 00:20:40,698
What?

263
00:20:40,865 --> 00:20:43,076
There's another fella on foot
up here on the road.

264
00:20:43,243 --> 00:20:45,453
Hey!

265
00:20:45,620 --> 00:20:47,413
What?!

266
00:20:47,581 --> 00:20:52,544
I said there's another fella on foot,
up here on the road.

267
00:21:09,644 --> 00:21:12,480
Hey! Hey!

268
00:21:12,647 --> 00:21:15,358
Considering there's a blizzard going on,

269
00:21:15,525 --> 00:21:18,696
whole lot of fellas walking around,
wouldn't you say, Major?

270
00:21:18,862 --> 00:21:23,033
Well, seeing as how I'm half of them fellas,
yeah, seems to be a lot of us.

271
00:21:23,199 --> 00:21:26,995
This changes things, son.

272
00:21:27,162 --> 00:21:30,623
$8,000 a lot of money for a nigger.

273
00:21:30,790 --> 00:21:32,875
With a partner, 18's a whole lot better.

274
00:21:33,043 --> 00:21:36,462
You really think
I'm in cahoots with that fella, or her?!

275
00:21:36,630 --> 00:21:39,341
- Put them on.
- I-I ain't wearing no handcuffs.

276
00:21:39,507 --> 00:21:41,384
You put those on, or you can stop

277
00:21:41,551 --> 00:21:43,845
worrying about this whole thing
right now!

278
00:21:45,013 --> 00:21:46,598
Hey!

279
00:21:58,026 --> 00:22:00,904
Hey!

280
00:22:06,660 --> 00:22:09,078
Hand your weapons to the driver.

281
00:22:09,245 --> 00:22:11,080
Little jumpy, ain't you?

282
00:22:11,247 --> 00:22:14,083
Never mind the jokes. Just do it.

283
00:22:14,250 --> 00:22:17,796
- If you say so.
- I do.

284
00:22:39,693 --> 00:22:41,527
Okay.

285
00:22:41,695 --> 00:22:44,907
- I done done it.
- O.B., you got 'em?

286
00:22:45,073 --> 00:22:47,910
- I got 'em.
- Okay, fella.

287
00:22:48,076 --> 00:22:50,411
You keep holding that lantern
in that one hand,

288
00:22:50,578 --> 00:22:53,665
and you keep that other hand
where I can see it.

289
00:22:53,832 --> 00:22:56,543
Walk over there
where I can get a good look at ya.

290
00:23:08,722 --> 00:23:12,475
Well, I'll be a goddamn dog in a manger.

291
00:23:12,642 --> 00:23:15,353
Is that you, Chris Mannix?

292
00:23:15,520 --> 00:23:18,482
- I'm sorry, friend, do we know each other?
- Not quite.

293
00:23:18,648 --> 00:23:22,152
- You know this fella?
- Only by reputation.

294
00:23:22,318 --> 00:23:26,280
Like I said, friend,
you got me at a bit of a disadvantage.

295
00:23:26,448 --> 00:23:30,077
Keeping you at a disadvantage
is an advantage I intend to keep.

296
00:23:30,243 --> 00:23:33,204
Whoever you are, mister,
you sure sound tough

297
00:23:33,371 --> 00:23:36,416
when you talking to a desperate man
knee-deep in snow.

298
00:23:36,583 --> 00:23:39,001
I-I... I don't want no trouble.

299
00:23:39,169 --> 00:23:42,590
I just want a ride.
I-I'm freezing to death!

300
00:23:42,756 --> 00:23:44,215
Who is this joker?

301
00:23:44,382 --> 00:23:48,928
You heard of the rebel renegade
Erskine Mannix?

302
00:23:49,095 --> 00:23:51,013
- Mannix's Marauders?
- That's them.

303
00:23:51,181 --> 00:23:54,183
Scourge of South Carolina,
Mannix's Marauders.

304
00:23:54,350 --> 00:23:56,602
It's Erskine's youngest boy, Chris.

305
00:23:56,770 --> 00:23:58,980
Brings you in my path, Chris Mannix?

306
00:23:59,147 --> 00:24:02,483
Well, Mr. Face, I was riding to Red Rock,

307
00:24:02,650 --> 00:24:04,986
my horse stepped in
a gopher hole in the snow,

308
00:24:05,153 --> 00:24:07,405
fucked up his leg, had to put 'er down.

309
00:24:07,572 --> 00:24:08,990
You got business in Red Rock?

310
00:24:09,157 --> 00:24:10,616
- Yes, I do.
- What?

311
00:24:10,784 --> 00:24:12,326
I'm the new sheriff.

312
00:24:12,494 --> 00:24:13,953
Horseshit.

313
00:24:14,120 --> 00:24:15,955
- 'Fraid not.
- Where's your star?

314
00:24:16,122 --> 00:24:17,707
Well, I ain't the sheriff yet.

315
00:24:17,874 --> 00:24:21,378
Now, once I get there, they swear me in.
But that ain't happened yet.

316
00:24:21,544 --> 00:24:23,004
And-and that's when you get your star.

317
00:24:23,171 --> 00:24:25,298
You got anything
that can back any of this up?

318
00:24:25,465 --> 00:24:27,633
Yeah. When we get to Red Rock.

319
00:24:27,801 --> 00:24:30,720
And-and from the look
of those three frozen fuckers up there,

320
00:24:30,887 --> 00:24:33,389
I-I figure you a bounty hunter
open for business.

321
00:24:33,556 --> 00:24:37,520
And-and I figure you taking them
three dead bodies into Red Rock to get paid?

322
00:24:37,685 --> 00:24:39,855
Three dead. One alive.

323
00:24:41,022 --> 00:24:43,651
- Who's that?
- Daisy Domergue.

324
00:24:43,817 --> 00:24:45,818
Who the fuck is Daisy Domergue?

325
00:24:45,985 --> 00:24:49,447
Not a goddamn thing to nobody,
except me and the hangman.

326
00:24:49,614 --> 00:24:51,075
The hangman?

327
00:24:53,451 --> 00:24:56,704
Well, I'll be double-dog damned.

328
00:24:56,871 --> 00:24:58,331
You're "The Hangman" Bob Ruth!

329
00:24:58,498 --> 00:24:59,582
It's John.

330
00:24:59,749 --> 00:25:01,918
And you!

331
00:25:02,085 --> 00:25:03,711
You're the nigger with the head!

332
00:25:03,878 --> 00:25:05,838
Major Marquis!

333
00:25:06,005 --> 00:25:08,090
My Lord, is that really the real head

334
00:25:08,258 --> 00:25:10,468
of Major Marquis looking at me now?

335
00:25:10,635 --> 00:25:13,054
Yeah, it's really me,
and it's really my head.

336
00:25:13,221 --> 00:25:14,847
So what's going on?

337
00:25:15,014 --> 00:25:18,269
Y'all having a bounty hunters' picnic?
Never mind.

338
00:25:18,434 --> 00:25:22,106
You taking them three dead bodies and-and
hurrying to Red Rock to get paid, ain't you?

339
00:25:22,272 --> 00:25:23,439
Yeah.

340
00:25:23,606 --> 00:25:28,696
Well, the man in Red Rock's
supposed to pay you is me, the new sheriff.

341
00:25:28,862 --> 00:25:30,571
So if y'all want to get paid,

342
00:25:30,738 --> 00:25:32,698
y'all need to get me to Red Rock.

343
00:25:32,866 --> 00:25:34,700
Well, excuse me
for finding it hard to believe

344
00:25:34,868 --> 00:25:38,371
a town electing you to do
anything except drop dead.

345
00:25:38,538 --> 00:25:42,459
So I'm supposed to freeze to death
'cause you find something hard to believe?

346
00:25:46,212 --> 00:25:48,131
No, I suppose not.

347
00:25:52,969 --> 00:25:54,929
Put them on and come inside.

348
00:26:01,936 --> 00:26:03,771
No.

349
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:08,818
Then you'll freeze.

350
00:26:08,985 --> 00:26:10,570
Then you'll hang.

351
00:26:10,737 --> 00:26:12,738
How so?

352
00:26:12,906 --> 00:26:16,951
Stagecoach driver,
could you come down here and join us?

353
00:26:17,118 --> 00:26:20,789
I got to hold these horses.
I can hear you just fine from up here.

354
00:26:20,955 --> 00:26:26,128
Well, you just heard me tell this fella
I'm the new sheriff of Red Rock, right?

355
00:26:26,294 --> 00:26:29,757
- Yeah.
- Red Rock is my town now.

356
00:26:29,923 --> 00:26:32,300
And I'm gonna enter my town
in bounty hunter's chains?

357
00:26:32,467 --> 00:26:33,759
No, sir!

358
00:26:33,927 --> 00:26:37,515
Sorry, bushwhackers,
I ain't entering Red Rock that way.

359
00:26:37,680 --> 00:26:39,390
Now, when you finally get to Red Rock,

360
00:26:39,557 --> 00:26:42,393
you gonna realize
every goddamn thing I said was right.

361
00:26:42,560 --> 00:26:44,812
And I expect you, O.B.,

362
00:26:44,979 --> 00:26:47,315
to tell the townsfolk of Red Rock

363
00:26:47,482 --> 00:26:50,276
that John Ruth
let their new sheriff freeze to death.

364
00:26:50,443 --> 00:26:55,533
Ain't no bounty on my head, bushwhacker.
You let me die, that's murder.

365
00:27:03,665 --> 00:27:05,625
Hold out your hands.

366
00:27:07,335 --> 00:27:09,170
O.B.!

367
00:27:09,337 --> 00:27:11,297
Give the major back his iron.

368
00:27:13,007 --> 00:27:14,717
One thing I know for sure,

369
00:27:14,884 --> 00:27:16,552
this nigger-hating son of a gun

370
00:27:16,719 --> 00:27:18,804
ain't partnered up with you.

371
00:27:18,972 --> 00:27:22,016
Now, I'll help you protect your 8,000,

372
00:27:22,183 --> 00:27:24,185
you help me protect my ten.

373
00:27:24,352 --> 00:27:26,020
Deal?

374
00:27:27,563 --> 00:27:29,398
Well, ain't love grand?

375
00:27:29,565 --> 00:27:32,824
Y'all want to lie on the ground
and make snow angels together?

376
00:27:35,279 --> 00:27:37,448
Come on!

377
00:27:43,329 --> 00:27:46,208
- Well, I'll tell you what, Bob.
- The name's John.

378
00:27:46,374 --> 00:27:49,713
When we get to Red Rock, I'll buy you
and Major Marquis there dinner and booze.

379
00:27:49,879 --> 00:27:51,003
Get in!

380
00:27:51,170 --> 00:27:54,884
- My way of saying thanks.
- I don't drink with rebel renegades,

381
00:27:55,049 --> 00:27:57,468
and I damn sure
don't break bread with them.

382
00:27:57,635 --> 00:27:59,637
- Well, Mr. Ruth...
- Get up, boys!

383
00:27:59,804 --> 00:28:02,850
You sound like you got a axe
to grind against the Cause.

384
00:28:03,016 --> 00:28:05,893
- "The Cause" of a renegade army?
- Get in!

385
00:28:06,060 --> 00:28:08,062
Bunch of losers gone loco.

386
00:28:08,229 --> 00:28:09,897
- You bet I do.
- Get up there!

387
00:28:10,064 --> 00:28:13,194
You wrapped yourselves up in a rebel flag
as an excuse to kill and steal.

388
00:28:13,359 --> 00:28:15,695
And this ought to interest you, Warren.

389
00:28:15,862 --> 00:28:18,197
Imparticular, emancipated blacks.

390
00:28:18,364 --> 00:28:20,117
Sounds like my kind of fella.

391
00:28:22,452 --> 00:28:23,995
Sound to me you been reading

392
00:28:24,162 --> 00:28:27,915
a lot of newspapers
printed in Washington, D.C.

393
00:28:28,082 --> 00:28:31,002
- Get in!
- Anywho, I'm just trying

394
00:28:31,169 --> 00:28:33,212
to let y'all know how grateful I am.

395
00:28:33,379 --> 00:28:36,383
I was a goner. And y'all saved me.

396
00:28:36,549 --> 00:28:38,801
You want to show me
how grateful you are?

397
00:28:38,968 --> 00:28:40,720
- Get in there!
- Shut up.

398
00:28:42,346 --> 00:28:46,477
Goddamn it, Daisy. It's coming.

399
00:28:46,642 --> 00:28:49,230
- Get in there, Cimarron!
- Here.

400
00:28:49,395 --> 00:28:53,150
- Last piece.
- Get in!

401
00:28:53,316 --> 00:28:55,610
Get in, now!

402
00:28:57,945 --> 00:28:59,781
Does he know...

403
00:29:01,657 --> 00:29:04,535
Does he know
how famous you once was?

404
00:29:04,702 --> 00:29:07,581
- I don't think so.
- Giddyup!

405
00:29:07,747 --> 00:29:09,373
Black Eye.

406
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:12,460
- Do you know who he is?
- Get in!

407
00:29:12,627 --> 00:29:15,046
Do I know about the $30,000 reward

408
00:29:15,213 --> 00:29:17,506
the Confederacy put
on the head of Major Marquis?

409
00:29:17,673 --> 00:29:19,216
Come on now, boys!

410
00:29:19,383 --> 00:29:20,760
- Get in!
- Yeah.

411
00:29:20,927 --> 00:29:23,056
- Them hillbillies went nigger head-hunting.
- Get in!

412
00:29:23,223 --> 00:29:25,724
They just never did get 'em
the right nigger head, did they?

413
00:29:25,890 --> 00:29:27,767
No, they didn't.

414
00:29:27,934 --> 00:29:30,980
- But it wasn't for lack of trying.
- Get in, boys! Get on!

415
00:29:31,145 --> 00:29:32,855
Them peckerwoods
left their homes and families,

416
00:29:33,022 --> 00:29:35,816
and come up this snowy mountain
looking for me and fortune.

417
00:29:35,983 --> 00:29:37,735
Get up!

418
00:29:37,902 --> 00:29:39,445
Ain't none of 'em found fortune.

419
00:29:39,612 --> 00:29:42,490
The ones
you ain't never heard of no more,

420
00:29:42,657 --> 00:29:44,366
they found me.

421
00:29:44,534 --> 00:29:46,702
Now, it didn't stay $30,000
the length of the war.

422
00:29:46,869 --> 00:29:49,665
Once passions cooled,
it dropped down to eight, then five.

423
00:29:49,831 --> 00:29:50,956
Get up, boys!

424
00:29:51,124 --> 00:29:53,209
But I bet even when it was 5,000,

425
00:29:53,376 --> 00:29:55,961
you had your share
of country boys coming to call.

426
00:29:56,129 --> 00:29:59,215
You know I did.

427
00:29:59,382 --> 00:30:01,967
Why'd they have a reward on you?

428
00:30:02,135 --> 00:30:04,512
Confederates took exception
to my capacity for killing 'em.

429
00:30:04,679 --> 00:30:06,013
Get up, now!

430
00:30:06,180 --> 00:30:08,224
And after I broke out of Wellenbeck,

431
00:30:08,391 --> 00:30:11,648
well, the South took my continued existence
as a personal affront.

432
00:30:11,815 --> 00:30:12,978
Get up!

433
00:30:13,146 --> 00:30:15,981
And the Cause put a reward on my head.

434
00:30:16,149 --> 00:30:19,778
- Get in there!
- What's Wellenbeck?

435
00:30:19,944 --> 00:30:22,907
You ain't never heard of Wellenbeck
prisoner of war camp, West Virginia?

436
00:30:23,072 --> 00:30:24,865
No, reb, I ain't never heard of it.

437
00:30:25,032 --> 00:30:26,868
Did you bust out?

438
00:30:28,536 --> 00:30:31,747
Major Marquis did more than bust out.

439
00:30:31,914 --> 00:30:33,582
Major Marquis had a bright idea.

440
00:30:33,749 --> 00:30:34,792
Get in, now!

441
00:30:34,959 --> 00:30:37,211
So bright, you got to wonder

442
00:30:37,378 --> 00:30:39,714
why nobody never thought about it before.

443
00:30:41,215 --> 00:30:43,259
Tell John Ruth your bright idea.

444
00:30:45,094 --> 00:30:48,891
Well, the whole damn place
was just made out of kindling.

445
00:30:49,056 --> 00:30:50,516
Get in!

446
00:30:50,794 --> 00:30:52,508
So I burnt it down.

447
00:30:54,478 --> 00:30:56,564
Get in!

448
00:30:58,441 --> 00:31:01,944
There was a rookie regiment
spending overnight in the camp.

449
00:31:02,111 --> 00:31:05,114
47 men burnt to a crisp.

450
00:31:05,281 --> 00:31:08,284
- Southern youth, farmers' sons,
- Get up!

451
00:31:08,451 --> 00:31:11,247
- Cream of the crop.
- And I say, "Let 'em burn."

452
00:31:11,412 --> 00:31:14,832
I'm supposed to apologize
for killing Johnny Reb?

453
00:31:14,999 --> 00:31:17,668
You joined the war
to keep niggers in chains.

454
00:31:17,835 --> 00:31:20,090
I joined the war
to kill white Southern crackers.

455
00:31:20,257 --> 00:31:21,380
Get up!

456
00:31:21,547 --> 00:31:23,549
And that means killing 'em any way I can.

457
00:31:23,716 --> 00:31:25,801
- Get in!
- Shoot 'em, stab 'em,

458
00:31:25,968 --> 00:31:27,761
drown 'em, burn 'em,

459
00:31:27,929 --> 00:31:30,222
drop a big ol' rock on their head.

460
00:31:30,389 --> 00:31:32,604
Whatever it took to put
white Southern crackers in the ground.

461
00:31:32,771 --> 00:31:33,809
Get up!

462
00:31:33,976 --> 00:31:37,064
That's what I joined the war to do.
And that's what I did.

463
00:31:37,230 --> 00:31:39,231
To answer your question, John Ruth,

464
00:31:39,398 --> 00:31:43,235
when Major Marquis burned 47 men alive,

465
00:31:43,402 --> 00:31:46,155
for no more reason
than to give a nigger a run for the trees,

466
00:31:46,322 --> 00:31:49,493
that's when the South put a reward
on the head of Major Marquis.

467
00:31:49,659 --> 00:31:51,368
- And I made them trees, Mannix.
- Get in!

468
00:31:51,535 --> 00:31:55,082
You best believe I ain't looked back
till I crossed the Northern line.

469
00:31:55,248 --> 00:31:59,128
But you had a surprise waiting for you
on the Northern side, didn't you?

470
00:31:59,293 --> 00:32:03,632
See, once they started pulling out
all them burnt bodies at Wellenbeck,

471
00:32:03,798 --> 00:32:06,091
seems not all them boys were rebs.

472
00:32:06,259 --> 00:32:09,136
Why, you burn up
some of your own boys,

473
00:32:09,303 --> 00:32:10,596
didn't you, Major?

474
00:32:10,763 --> 00:32:13,098
How many burnt prisoners
they end up finding?

475
00:32:13,266 --> 00:32:17,605
Wasn't the final Yankee death count
something like 37?

476
00:32:17,770 --> 00:32:19,104
Giddyup!

477
00:32:19,272 --> 00:32:22,484
That's the thing about war, Mannix.
People die.

478
00:32:24,068 --> 00:32:27,112
So you gonna chalk it up to "war is hell"?

479
00:32:27,280 --> 00:32:29,657
Well, admittedly,
that is a hard argument to argue with.

480
00:32:29,824 --> 00:32:31,659
But if memory serves,

481
00:32:31,826 --> 00:32:35,120
your side didn't look at it that way.

482
00:32:35,288 --> 00:32:37,665
I think they thought 37 white men

483
00:32:37,832 --> 00:32:40,125
for one nigger

484
00:32:40,293 --> 00:32:42,419
wasn't so hot a trade.

485
00:32:42,586 --> 00:32:45,798
- I do believe they accused you
- Giddyup!

486
00:32:45,965 --> 00:32:49,428
Of being a kill-crazy nigger
who only joined the war to kill white folks,

487
00:32:49,593 --> 00:32:52,348
and the whole blue and gray of it all
really didn't matter that much to you.

488
00:32:52,513 --> 00:32:53,889
Get up!

489
00:32:54,056 --> 00:32:56,016
And that's why
they drummed your black ass

490
00:32:56,183 --> 00:32:58,519
out of the cavalry
with a yellow stripe down your back.

491
00:32:58,686 --> 00:33:01,814
- Get in!
- Isn't it, Major?

492
00:33:01,981 --> 00:33:03,274
Horseshit!

493
00:33:03,441 --> 00:33:05,152
If he'd have did all that,
the cavalry would've shot him.

494
00:33:05,320 --> 00:33:07,988
- Get in!
- Well, I didn't say they could prove it.

495
00:33:08,154 --> 00:33:09,194
Get up!

496
00:33:09,361 --> 00:33:11,490
But they sure did think it out loud,
didn't they, Major?

497
00:33:11,657 --> 00:33:13,450
Get up, boys!

498
00:33:13,617 --> 00:33:16,203
But Warren's war record was stellar,

499
00:33:16,370 --> 00:33:18,748
and that's what saved his ass.

500
00:33:20,124 --> 00:33:21,875
Now, you killed yourself your share

501
00:33:22,043 --> 00:33:26,297
of redskins in your day,
didn't you, Black Major?

502
00:33:26,464 --> 00:33:28,424
Cavalry tends to look kindly on that.

503
00:33:28,591 --> 00:33:31,427
I'll tell you what the cavalry
didn't look kindly on.

504
00:33:31,594 --> 00:33:33,641
- Giddyup!
- Mannix's Marauders, that's what.

505
00:33:33,808 --> 00:33:34,847
Get in!

506
00:33:35,014 --> 00:33:39,061
And the fact that Erskine Mannix's little boy
would talk about anybody else's behavior

507
00:33:39,226 --> 00:33:42,605
during war time
makes me want to horse-laugh.

508
00:33:44,106 --> 00:33:47,192
Don't you say anything about my daddy.

509
00:33:47,360 --> 00:33:50,696
- What he fought for was dignity in defeat,
- Get up there!

510
00:33:50,863 --> 00:33:53,115
And against the unconditional surrender.

511
00:33:53,282 --> 00:33:56,702
We weren't foreign barbarians
pounding on the city walls.

512
00:33:56,869 --> 00:33:58,829
We were your brothers.

513
00:33:58,996 --> 00:34:00,289
Get up, now!

514
00:34:00,456 --> 00:34:02,207
We deserved dignity in defeat.

515
00:34:02,375 --> 00:34:05,085
Just how many nigger towns did y'all sack

516
00:34:05,252 --> 00:34:07,629
in your fight for dignity in defeat?

517
00:34:07,797 --> 00:34:10,049
Ny fair share, Black Major.

518
00:34:10,216 --> 00:34:12,760
'Cause when niggers are scared,

519
00:34:12,927 --> 00:34:14,804
That's when white folks are safe.

520
00:34:16,555 --> 00:34:19,391
You gonna talk that hateful nigger talk,

521
00:34:19,558 --> 00:34:22,728
you can ride up top with O.B.

522
00:34:22,895 --> 00:34:24,063
No.

523
00:34:24,230 --> 00:34:25,731
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

524
00:34:25,898 --> 00:34:28,317
You done got me talking politics.

525
00:34:28,484 --> 00:34:30,569
I didn't want to.

526
00:34:30,736 --> 00:34:33,739
Like I said, y'all,
I'm just happy to be alive.

527
00:34:33,906 --> 00:34:35,908
Get in, now!

528
00:34:36,075 --> 00:34:37,910
Get up!

529
00:34:38,077 --> 00:34:41,121
I think I'll scoot over here
right by this window,

530
00:34:41,288 --> 00:34:45,751
and let this beautiful carriage
rock me to sleep.

531
00:34:45,918 --> 00:34:48,712
And dream about how lucky I am.

532
00:34:52,425 --> 00:34:54,385
Get up, now!

533
00:35:44,602 --> 00:35:46,311
Get in!

534
00:35:46,479 --> 00:35:49,108
Get in there! Get in!

535
00:35:49,273 --> 00:35:52,319
Get in there! Get in!

536
00:35:52,485 --> 00:35:54,194
Get in there, Leche!

537
00:35:54,361 --> 00:35:56,113
Get in there!

538
00:35:56,280 --> 00:35:59,366
Easy.

539
00:36:24,141 --> 00:36:25,684
What the hell is going on?

540
00:36:25,851 --> 00:36:28,729
We weren't expecting
another stage tonight!

541
00:36:28,896 --> 00:36:32,900
Yeah, I can see
you already got another one up in here.

542
00:36:33,067 --> 00:36:35,652
Just got through putting the horses away.

543
00:36:35,819 --> 00:36:37,488
Well, this ain't the normal line,

544
00:36:37,655 --> 00:36:40,491
but we are stuck
on the wrong side of a blizzard,

545
00:36:40,658 --> 00:36:42,868
so it looks like you're stuck with us.

546
00:36:43,035 --> 00:36:44,953
Are Minnie and Sweet Dave inside?

547
00:36:45,120 --> 00:36:46,580
They ain't here.

548
00:36:46,747 --> 00:36:48,999
I'm running the place while they're gone.

549
00:36:50,751 --> 00:36:52,669
Where's Minnie and Sweet Dave?

550
00:36:52,836 --> 00:36:54,630
He says they ain't here.

551
00:36:54,797 --> 00:36:56,965
He's looking after the place
while they're gone.

552
00:36:57,132 --> 00:36:59,510
Who are you?

553
00:37:01,595 --> 00:37:03,015
I'm Bob.

554
00:37:05,140 --> 00:37:09,269
Well, whoever you are,
help O.B. with the horses.

555
00:37:09,436 --> 00:37:11,396
Come on.

556
00:37:11,564 --> 00:37:14,525
Get 'em out of this cold
'fore that blizzard hits us.

557
00:37:14,692 --> 00:37:17,152
You all right?

558
00:37:17,319 --> 00:37:19,573
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait!
Esperate, esperate, esperate!

559
00:37:19,738 --> 00:37:22,074
I just put those other horses away.

560
00:37:22,241 --> 00:37:25,244
You need it done fast,
you need to help.

561
00:37:25,411 --> 00:37:27,913
I got two of my best men on it.

562
00:37:29,164 --> 00:37:31,416
You heard him, freeloaders.

563
00:37:31,584 --> 00:37:33,669
Get to work!

564
00:37:33,836 --> 00:37:36,296
All right, you two, unhook the leaders.

565
00:37:36,463 --> 00:37:39,426
- Come on, let's go.
- Open up!

566
00:37:39,592 --> 00:37:41,051
- You have to kick it open!
- Ya got to kick it open!

567
00:37:41,218 --> 00:37:43,639
- What?
- Kick it open!

568
00:37:43,804 --> 00:37:45,556
Shut that door.

569
00:37:45,723 --> 00:37:48,352
- There's a goddamn blizzard out there!
- You have to stop, close the door!

570
00:37:48,517 --> 00:37:52,606
- You got to nail it shut.
- You have to, you have to nail it shut!

571
00:37:52,771 --> 00:37:54,106
Hold it shut!

572
00:37:54,273 --> 00:37:57,444
- There's a hammer and nails by the door!
- You have to nail it shut!

573
00:37:57,610 --> 00:38:00,654
There's a hammer and nails by the door.

574
00:38:00,821 --> 00:38:02,698
- Give me a hammer.
- Yeah.

575
00:38:11,624 --> 00:38:13,166
You need,
you need two pieces of wood!

576
00:38:13,334 --> 00:38:15,002
You need two pieces of wood!
One ain't good enough!

577
00:38:15,169 --> 00:38:18,841
- Two pieces of wood!
- The fuckin' thing is busted!

578
00:38:19,006 --> 00:38:21,675
Not just one piece of wood!

579
00:38:21,842 --> 00:38:25,264
- Give me another piece of wood.
- Yeah. All right.

580
00:38:29,725 --> 00:38:31,352
- I need a nail.
- Here.

581
00:38:44,323 --> 00:38:45,908
Jesus.

582
00:38:48,827 --> 00:38:50,996
That door's a son of a gun.

583
00:38:51,163 --> 00:38:55,002
Who's the idiot who broke that,
that Mexican fella?

584
00:38:55,167 --> 00:38:57,922
Good heavens. A woman?

585
00:38:58,087 --> 00:39:02,718
Out in this white hell?
You must be frozen solid, poor thing.

586
00:39:04,426 --> 00:39:07,137
Looks like Minnie's got her a full house.

587
00:39:09,473 --> 00:39:11,558
When did you fellas arrive?

588
00:39:12,851 --> 00:39:14,728
About 40 minutes ago.

589
00:39:14,895 --> 00:39:17,445
That cowboy fella in the corner,
that your driver?

590
00:39:17,612 --> 00:39:20,694
No, no, he's a passenger.
The driver lit out.

591
00:39:20,859 --> 00:39:23,823
Said he was going to spend the blizzard
shacked up with a friend.

592
00:39:23,987 --> 00:39:26,531
Lucky devil.

593
00:39:26,699 --> 00:39:28,784
Jesus Christ, that's awful!

594
00:39:28,951 --> 00:39:31,411
Christ Almighty,

595
00:39:31,578 --> 00:39:34,539
what'd that Mexican fella do,
soak his old socks in a pot?

596
00:39:34,707 --> 00:39:37,250
Yes... I-I think we all felt the same way,

597
00:39:37,418 --> 00:39:40,462
but were a little too polite
to say something.

598
00:39:40,629 --> 00:39:42,839
- He don't have that problem.
- Shit.

599
00:39:43,006 --> 00:39:44,633
Where's the well water?

600
00:39:44,800 --> 00:39:46,343
Over there.

601
00:39:52,224 --> 00:39:55,686
So, all three of you fellas
headed to Red Rock

602
00:39:55,853 --> 00:39:58,563
when the blizzard stopped you?

603
00:39:58,731 --> 00:40:01,900
Yes. All three of us
were on that stagecoach out there.

604
00:40:13,245 --> 00:40:15,789
Coffee beans.

605
00:40:15,956 --> 00:40:18,500
Over there.

606
00:40:26,592 --> 00:40:28,761
Get your hand out of there.

607
00:40:32,765 --> 00:40:35,434
New sheriff of Red Rock's
travelin' with us.

608
00:40:35,601 --> 00:40:38,437
Sheriff of Red Rock, that'll be the day.

609
00:40:38,604 --> 00:40:41,398
He's a goddamn sheriff,
I'm a monkey's uncle.

610
00:40:41,565 --> 00:40:42,607
Good.

611
00:40:42,775 --> 00:40:45,613
Then you can share bananas
with your nigger friend in the stable.

612
00:40:45,778 --> 00:40:47,988
So,

613
00:40:48,155 --> 00:40:50,323
the new sheriff of Red Rock
is traveling with you?

614
00:40:50,491 --> 00:40:53,829
He's lying.
He ain't sheriff of nothin'.

615
00:40:53,994 --> 00:40:55,871
He's a Southern renegade.

616
00:40:56,038 --> 00:40:59,543
He's just talking hisself
out of freezing to death is all.

617
00:40:59,708 --> 00:41:01,626
What the fuck I tell you about talking?

618
00:41:01,794 --> 00:41:05,633
I'll bust you in the mouth right in front
of these people. I don't give a fuck!

619
00:41:05,798 --> 00:41:09,553
- You never gave your name, sir.
- John Ruth.

620
00:41:09,718 --> 00:41:12,264
- Are you a lawman?
- I'm taking her to the law.

621
00:41:12,429 --> 00:41:16,143
- So you're a bounty hunter?
- That's right, buster.

622
00:41:18,227 --> 00:41:19,895
Do you have a warrant?

623
00:41:20,062 --> 00:41:22,775
- Yeah, course I do.
- May I see it?

624
00:41:26,151 --> 00:41:27,652
Why?

625
00:41:27,820 --> 00:41:30,864
You're supposed to produce it
upon request.

626
00:41:31,031 --> 00:41:33,700
How am I supposed to know
you're not a villain,

627
00:41:33,867 --> 00:41:36,203
kidnapping this woman,

628
00:41:36,370 --> 00:41:38,330
without a warrant in your possession?

629
00:41:40,415 --> 00:41:42,042
What's your name, buster?

630
00:41:42,209 --> 00:41:46,129
Well, it certainly isn't Buster.

631
00:41:47,422 --> 00:41:50,717
It's Oswaldo Mobray.

632
00:41:51,885 --> 00:41:53,220
Oswaldo?

633
00:41:53,387 --> 00:41:54,805
Yes.

634
00:41:56,014 --> 00:41:57,891
Well,

635
00:41:58,058 --> 00:42:01,353
I got my warrant, Oswaldo.

636
00:42:14,783 --> 00:42:15,867
I take it you're Daisy Domergue?

637
00:42:16,034 --> 00:42:17,619
- That's her.
- Yeah.

638
00:42:19,246 --> 00:42:20,873
I see.

639
00:42:22,499 --> 00:42:25,877
It says here "dead or alive."

640
00:42:26,044 --> 00:42:27,838
Yeah. It does.

641
00:42:28,005 --> 00:42:30,006
Well, transporting a desperate,

642
00:42:30,173 --> 00:42:32,551
hostile prisoner such as her

643
00:42:32,718 --> 00:42:34,511
sounds like hard work.

644
00:42:34,678 --> 00:42:39,143
Wouldn't transporting her be easier
if she were dead?

645
00:42:39,308 --> 00:42:41,935
Well, no one said
the job was supposed to be easy.

646
00:42:42,102 --> 00:42:44,563
And why is her hanging proper
so important to you?

647
00:42:44,730 --> 00:42:48,277
Let's just say I don't like cheatin'
the hangman. He got to make a living, too.

648
00:42:48,442 --> 00:42:50,777
Well, I appreciate that.

649
00:42:50,944 --> 00:42:53,780
Allow me to properly

650
00:42:53,947 --> 00:42:55,782
introduce myself.

651
00:42:55,949 --> 00:42:57,826
I'm Oswaldo Mobray,

652
00:42:57,993 --> 00:43:00,370
the hangman in these parts.

653
00:43:05,500 --> 00:43:07,335
La-di-da.

654
00:43:07,502 --> 00:43:10,174
- Looks like I brought you a customer.
- Yeah, so it would appear.

655
00:43:10,339 --> 00:43:15,262
You ever spent two days or more
locked up with one of your customers before?

656
00:43:15,427 --> 00:43:17,387
- I can't say I have.
- Don't talk to my prisoner.

657
00:43:17,554 --> 00:43:18,930
I talk to my prisoner, that's it.

658
00:43:19,097 --> 00:43:20,140
- You got it?
- I got it.

659
00:43:20,307 --> 00:43:21,433
Jolly good.

660
00:43:21,600 --> 00:43:25,064
You got anything in here besides coffee
that can help warm us up?

661
00:43:25,228 --> 00:43:27,355
Well, the bar is open.

662
00:43:27,522 --> 00:43:30,192
Follow moi.

663
00:43:42,663 --> 00:43:45,666
Line, O.B.!

664
00:44:12,484 --> 00:44:13,986
Hey.

665
00:44:28,000 --> 00:44:31,211
You're all right, you're all right.

666
00:44:31,378 --> 00:44:33,130
Come on, goddamn it. I'm cold!

667
00:44:39,594 --> 00:44:41,638
I'll feed and water the horses.

668
00:44:41,805 --> 00:44:44,724
You go inside and get some hot coffee.

669
00:44:44,891 --> 00:44:47,521
Got some stew cooking.
Should be done soon.

670
00:44:47,686 --> 00:44:48,895
Now, look.

671
00:44:49,062 --> 00:44:52,399
No matter how bad this blizzard gets,

672
00:44:52,566 --> 00:44:54,651
we still got to feed these horses

673
00:44:54,818 --> 00:44:57,362
and take a squat from time to time.

674
00:44:57,529 --> 00:45:00,573
So me and Chris better lay out a line

675
00:45:00,741 --> 00:45:02,867
from the stable to the front door

676
00:45:03,035 --> 00:45:05,870
and from the front door to the shithouse.

677
00:45:06,038 --> 00:45:07,539
Okay?

678
00:45:10,959 --> 00:45:12,586
Good idea.

679
00:45:13,712 --> 00:45:15,338
Come on, Chris.

680
00:45:17,049 --> 00:45:18,676
I'll give you a hand.

681
00:45:20,052 --> 00:45:22,679
No, no, no, no, no.
Go inside. Get warm.

682
00:45:22,846 --> 00:45:26,519
You're doin' stable work in a goddamn blizzard.
I offer to help, you say no?

683
00:45:28,101 --> 00:45:30,103
You're right, amigo.

684
00:45:30,270 --> 00:45:32,147
Muchas gracias.

685
00:45:34,357 --> 00:45:36,234
All right. Follow me.

686
00:45:47,120 --> 00:45:50,790
We're gonna drop one every ten paces,

687
00:45:50,957 --> 00:45:52,500
- from here to the door.
- Yeah!

688
00:45:52,667 --> 00:45:54,461
All right!

689
00:46:54,146 --> 00:46:57,649
Now, you're wanted for murder.

690
00:46:57,816 --> 00:46:59,818
For the sake of my analogy,

691
00:46:59,985 --> 00:47:01,986
let's just assume that you did it.

692
00:47:02,154 --> 00:47:06,243
Now, John Ruth wants to take you
back to Red Rock to stand trial for murder.

693
00:47:06,408 --> 00:47:09,494
And if you're found guilty,

694
00:47:09,661 --> 00:47:13,250
the people of Red Rock
will hang you in the town square.

695
00:47:13,415 --> 00:47:15,166
And, as the hangman,

696
00:47:15,333 --> 00:47:18,503
I will perform the execution.

697
00:47:18,670 --> 00:47:21,214
And if all those things

698
00:47:21,381 --> 00:47:23,174
end up taking place,

699
00:47:23,341 --> 00:47:26,302
that's what civilized society

700
00:47:26,469 --> 00:47:29,722
calls justice.

701
00:47:29,890 --> 00:47:31,724
However,

702
00:47:31,892 --> 00:47:35,019
if the relatives and the loved ones

703
00:47:35,187 --> 00:47:36,896
of the person you murdered

704
00:47:37,063 --> 00:47:41,028
were outside that door right now,
and after busting down that door,

705
00:47:41,193 --> 00:47:43,570
they drug you out into the snow

706
00:47:43,737 --> 00:47:45,738
and hung you up by the neck,

707
00:47:45,906 --> 00:47:49,200
that would be frontier justice.

708
00:47:49,367 --> 00:47:52,245
Now, the good part

709
00:47:52,412 --> 00:47:54,080
about frontier justice

710
00:47:54,247 --> 00:47:57,834
is it's very thirst-quenching.

711
00:47:58,001 --> 00:48:02,422
The bad part is
it's apt to be wrong as right.

712
00:48:02,589 --> 00:48:05,302
Well, not in your case.
In your case, you'd have it coming.

713
00:48:05,467 --> 00:48:08,553
But other people, maybe not so much.

714
00:48:08,720 --> 00:48:11,097
But ultimately, what's the real difference

715
00:48:11,264 --> 00:48:12,682
between the two?

716
00:48:12,849 --> 00:48:16,436
The real difference is me.

717
00:48:16,603 --> 00:48:18,062
The hangman.

718
00:48:18,230 --> 00:48:19,939
To me, it doesn't matter what you did.

719
00:48:20,106 --> 00:48:22,275
When I hang you,
I'll get no satisfaction from your death.

720
00:48:22,442 --> 00:48:25,072
It's my job.
I hang you in Red Rock.

721
00:48:25,237 --> 00:48:26,905
I move on to the next town.

722
00:48:27,072 --> 00:48:30,867
I hang someone else there.

723
00:48:31,034 --> 00:48:35,079
The man who pulls the lever
that breaks your neck

724
00:48:35,247 --> 00:48:38,082
will be a dispassionate man.

725
00:48:38,250 --> 00:48:42,503
And that dispassion
is the very essence of justice.

726
00:48:42,671 --> 00:48:46,424
For justice delivered without dis-passion

727
00:48:46,591 --> 00:48:51,179
is always in danger of not being justice.

728
00:48:51,346 --> 00:48:52,722
Amen.

729
00:49:17,998 --> 00:49:22,421
No offense, cowboy fella.
Just gettin' your attention.

730
00:49:22,585 --> 00:49:25,922
Yeah, well...

731
00:49:26,089 --> 00:49:27,966
you got it.

732
00:49:28,133 --> 00:49:30,718
What you writin', friend?

733
00:49:30,885 --> 00:49:33,137
Only thing I'm qualified to write about.

734
00:49:33,305 --> 00:49:35,431
What's that?

735
00:49:35,598 --> 00:49:37,517
My life story.

736
00:49:37,684 --> 00:49:39,352
You're writing your life story?

737
00:49:39,519 --> 00:49:42,358
- You bet I am.
- Am I in it?

738
00:49:44,441 --> 00:49:46,067
You just entered.

739
00:49:47,569 --> 00:49:49,153
Well, you like writing stories so much,

740
00:49:49,321 --> 00:49:52,119
why don't you tell me
the story that brings you here?

741
00:49:52,824 --> 00:49:54,325
Who's asking?

742
00:49:54,492 --> 00:49:56,327
I am. John Ruth.

743
00:49:56,494 --> 00:49:58,871
I'm bringing in this one to Red Rock
to hang.

744
00:49:59,039 --> 00:50:01,165
And ain't no way
I'm spending a couple of nights

745
00:50:01,333 --> 00:50:03,584
under a roof with somebody
I don't know who they are,

746
00:50:03,752 --> 00:50:05,211
and I don't know who you are.

747
00:50:05,378 --> 00:50:07,297
So, who are you?

748
00:50:07,464 --> 00:50:09,299
Joe Gage.

749
00:50:09,466 --> 00:50:11,384
- What?
- That's my name.

750
00:50:11,551 --> 00:50:14,598
- Joe Gage.
- Okay, Joe Gage.

751
00:50:14,763 --> 00:50:16,472
Why you going to Red Rock?

752
00:50:16,639 --> 00:50:18,599
I ain't, I ain't,
I ain't going to Red Rock.

753
00:50:18,767 --> 00:50:22,231
- Where you going?
- About nine miles outside of Red Rock.

754
00:50:22,395 --> 00:50:24,900
- What's there?
- My mother.

755
00:50:26,024 --> 00:50:29,405
- Your mother?
- Listen, I'm just a cowpuncher.

756
00:50:29,569 --> 00:50:33,573
I just got back from a long drive, and...

757
00:50:33,740 --> 00:50:38,202
and I wasn't
just an ass in a saddle this time.

758
00:50:38,370 --> 00:50:40,705
I was a partner.

759
00:50:40,872 --> 00:50:44,625
First time in my life
I made a pretty penny.

760
00:50:44,793 --> 00:50:46,294
And

761
00:50:46,461 --> 00:50:48,796
figured I'd come home

762
00:50:48,963 --> 00:50:50,631
and spend time with my mother

763
00:50:50,799 --> 00:50:52,467
for Christmas.

764
00:50:52,634 --> 00:50:54,135
Now, that's funny.

765
00:50:55,512 --> 00:50:58,934
'Cause you don't look like
the coming-home-for-Christmas type.

766
00:50:59,099 --> 00:51:02,602
Yeah, well

767
00:51:02,769 --> 00:51:05,855
you know, looks can be deceiving.

768
00:51:07,899 --> 00:51:10,818
Because I definitely am a

769
00:51:10,985 --> 00:51:14,864
coming-home-for-Christmas-
to-spend-time-with-Mother type.

770
00:51:16,157 --> 00:51:20,244
Christmas with Mother, I mean,

771
00:51:20,412 --> 00:51:22,414
it's a wonderful thing.

772
00:51:23,957 --> 00:51:26,292
Now, is that

773
00:51:26,459 --> 00:51:28,086
good enough for you,

774
00:51:28,253 --> 00:51:30,547
John Ruth?

775
00:51:31,798 --> 00:51:33,758
For now.

776
00:51:33,925 --> 00:51:36,469
You steer clear of my prisoner.

777
00:51:40,849 --> 00:51:42,976
Hello, old-timer.

778
00:51:44,936 --> 00:51:46,521
General.

779
00:51:47,772 --> 00:51:49,190
General.

780
00:51:50,692 --> 00:51:54,028
You, sir, are a hyena.

781
00:51:55,864 --> 00:51:58,158
I have no wish to speak to you.

782
00:52:02,787 --> 00:52:04,914
I've been called worse.

783
00:52:07,000 --> 00:52:09,169
Fair enough, General.

784
00:52:10,462 --> 00:52:12,088
Sorry to bother you.

785
00:52:14,132 --> 00:52:15,633
Hey!

786
00:52:15,800 --> 00:52:17,510
- You gotta kick it open!
- Gotta kick it open!

787
00:52:17,677 --> 00:52:19,345
- What?
- Kick it open!

788
00:52:19,512 --> 00:52:22,480
- That latch, you gotta kick it open!
- You gotta kick it open!

789
00:52:22,640 --> 00:52:23,808
Jesus Christ!

790
00:52:23,975 --> 00:52:25,309
- Close it!
- Close it!

791
00:52:25,477 --> 00:52:26,727
- Close the door!
- What?

792
00:52:26,895 --> 00:52:28,312
- Close it!
- The goddamn door!

793
00:52:28,480 --> 00:52:31,823
- It doesn't have a latch. Close it!
- It's already cold enough in here!

794
00:52:35,236 --> 00:52:36,904
Doesn't have a latch.

795
00:52:37,071 --> 00:52:38,823
- You gotta hammer up a board.
- You gotta nail it shut!

796
00:52:38,990 --> 00:52:42,830
- The hammer and nails by the door.
- There's a hammer and nails right there!

797
00:52:42,994 --> 00:52:45,079
God!

798
00:52:45,246 --> 00:52:47,582
- Hold this here, Chris.
- Here! Here.

799
00:52:55,381 --> 00:52:56,757
- Watch your fingers.
- Yeah.

800
00:52:56,925 --> 00:52:58,676
- Really nail it in!
- Yeah.

801
00:53:01,304 --> 00:53:02,972
You need two pieces of wood.

802
00:53:03,139 --> 00:53:04,849
You got to hammer another one.

803
00:53:05,016 --> 00:53:06,726
One ain't good enough!

804
00:53:06,893 --> 00:53:08,769
It's gonna blow right open!

805
00:53:08,937 --> 00:53:11,859
- Now, goddamn it!
- Gonna open if you don't ham...!

806
00:53:12,023 --> 00:53:13,524
- Shut up!
- Got it!

807
00:53:13,691 --> 00:53:15,985
Son of a bitch!

808
00:53:27,789 --> 00:53:29,081
Jesus Christ.

809
00:53:29,249 --> 00:53:31,125
That's door's a whore.

810
00:53:35,338 --> 00:53:36,923
I get it. "Haberdashery."

811
00:53:37,090 --> 00:53:38,883
That was a joke.

812
00:53:39,050 --> 00:53:41,302
How's the coffee?

813
00:53:41,469 --> 00:53:45,014
Now?
Pretty good, if I do say so myself.

814
00:53:47,559 --> 00:53:49,102
Thank you.

815
00:54:03,658 --> 00:54:05,952
Navajo!

816
00:54:06,119 --> 00:54:07,870
Guess who he is.

817
00:54:09,789 --> 00:54:11,999
Buffalo Bill?

818
00:54:12,166 --> 00:54:13,751
Hardly.

819
00:54:13,918 --> 00:54:15,586
No. I'm...

820
00:54:15,753 --> 00:54:17,421
Oswaldo Mobray. I'm the...

821
00:54:17,589 --> 00:54:19,632
He's the hangman of Red Rock.

822
00:54:20,717 --> 00:54:21,842
You are?

823
00:54:22,010 --> 00:54:24,011
- Yes, I am.
- Well!

824
00:54:24,178 --> 00:54:26,681
- Good to meet you,
- Yeah.

825
00:54:26,848 --> 00:54:28,266
- Mr...?
- Mobray.

826
00:54:28,433 --> 00:54:29,433
- Mobray.
- Yeah.

827
00:54:29,601 --> 00:54:32,148
I'm Chris Mannix.
The new sheriff in Red Rock.

828
00:54:32,312 --> 00:54:34,480
- Really?
- Horseshit!

829
00:54:34,647 --> 00:54:37,653
- Pay no attention to him.
- Horseshit!

830
00:54:37,817 --> 00:54:42,074
Fella warmin' himself by that potbelly stove
is a hell of a driver named O.B.

831
00:54:42,238 --> 00:54:44,825
That's the only thing you've said
that's the truth.

832
00:54:46,242 --> 00:54:48,286
You comin' into Red Rock
to hang Lance Lawson?

833
00:54:48,453 --> 00:54:50,454
- Precisely.
- Do you have the execution orders on you?

834
00:54:50,622 --> 00:54:52,164
- In my bag.
- May I see 'em?

835
00:54:52,332 --> 00:54:53,916
Of course.

836
00:54:59,047 --> 00:55:01,215
Who's who's Lance Lawson?

837
00:55:01,382 --> 00:55:03,718
He's a fella
been sittin' in the Red Rock jail

838
00:55:03,885 --> 00:55:05,344
about a month now.

839
00:55:05,511 --> 00:55:07,513
He's the fella who shot the fella

840
00:55:07,680 --> 00:55:10,182
who was sheriff 'fore me.

841
00:55:10,350 --> 00:55:12,602
Precisely.

842
00:55:14,312 --> 00:55:16,397
Thank you.

843
00:55:21,694 --> 00:55:24,238
What did she mean when she said,

844
00:55:24,405 --> 00:55:27,199
"The bounty hunter's nigger friend
in the stable"?

845
00:55:27,367 --> 00:55:30,578
He's got a nigger bounty hunter friend
in the stable.

846
00:55:30,745 --> 00:55:32,830
But all that just to guard her?

847
00:55:32,997 --> 00:55:36,083
I don't think
that was the original idea, but...

848
00:55:36,250 --> 00:55:38,794
that's the idea now.

849
00:55:38,961 --> 00:55:41,213
Want a little snake bite in your coffee?

850
00:55:41,381 --> 00:55:43,090
Yeah.

851
00:55:43,257 --> 00:55:44,717
Five of you?

852
00:55:44,884 --> 00:55:46,844
Well, well, well,
looks like Minnie's Haberdashery

853
00:55:47,011 --> 00:55:49,388
is about to get cozy
for the next few days.

854
00:55:49,555 --> 00:55:51,057
Yes, it does.

855
00:55:54,727 --> 00:55:56,145
Here.

856
00:56:00,191 --> 00:56:03,361
Are you the chap with the Lincoln letter?

857
00:56:03,528 --> 00:56:05,279
The Lincoln what?

858
00:56:05,446 --> 00:56:08,908
Yes. The letter from Abraham Lincoln.

859
00:56:09,075 --> 00:56:11,035
President Abraham Lincoln?

860
00:56:11,202 --> 00:56:13,913
Yes. Weren't you pen pals?

861
00:56:14,080 --> 00:56:16,248
With the president?

862
00:56:16,416 --> 00:56:19,377
Well, I'm sorry,
I heard that somebody in your party

863
00:56:19,544 --> 00:56:21,253
had a letter from Abraham Lincoln.

864
00:56:21,421 --> 00:56:24,260
- I assumed it was you.
- Not him!

865
00:56:24,424 --> 00:56:27,051
Black fella in the stable.

866
00:56:27,218 --> 00:56:28,636
The nigger...

867
00:56:28,803 --> 00:56:32,056
in the stable
has a letter from Abraham Lincoln?

868
00:56:32,223 --> 00:56:33,808
Yeah.

869
00:56:33,975 --> 00:56:38,688
The nigger in the stable
has a letter from Abraham Lincoln?

870
00:56:53,745 --> 00:56:55,955
What'd you say your name was again?

871
00:56:56,122 --> 00:56:57,957
- Bob.
- Warren.

872
00:56:58,124 --> 00:57:00,334
Minnie and Sweet Dave in there?

873
00:57:00,501 --> 00:57:04,466
Minnie and Sweet Dave went to visit her mother
on the north side of the mountain.

874
00:57:04,630 --> 00:57:06,006
- What?
- Yeah.

875
00:57:06,174 --> 00:57:10,097
- Minnie ain't here?
- Yes, they're visiting her mother.

876
00:57:10,261 --> 00:57:12,346
- Her mother?
- Yes.

877
00:57:15,475 --> 00:57:17,769
Never knew Minnie had a mother.

878
00:57:19,979 --> 00:57:22,857
Well, everybody's got a mother.

879
00:57:24,358 --> 00:57:26,277
Yeah, I suppose.

880
00:57:29,155 --> 00:57:31,282
And she left you in charge?

881
00:57:31,449 --> 00:57:32,825
Si.

882
00:57:34,952 --> 00:57:37,955
That sure don't sound like Minnie.

883
00:57:38,122 --> 00:57:40,374
Are you calling me a liar?

884
00:57:42,335 --> 00:57:44,754
Well, not yet I ain't.

885
00:57:44,921 --> 00:57:47,131
Just sounds peculiar is all.

886
00:57:47,298 --> 00:57:49,133
What sounds peculiar?

887
00:57:49,300 --> 00:57:51,302
Well, first off, Minnie never struck me

888
00:57:51,469 --> 00:57:53,220
as the sentimental type.

889
00:57:53,387 --> 00:57:57,141
And secondly, I can't imagine
Sweet Dave lifting his fat ass

890
00:57:57,308 --> 00:57:58,976
out his chair
long enough to fetch well water

891
00:57:59,143 --> 00:58:01,353
unless Minnie was laying
a frying pan upside his head,

892
00:58:01,521 --> 00:58:03,481
let alone take a trip to the north side.

893
00:58:03,648 --> 00:58:05,858
Well, that sounds a whole lot

894
00:58:06,025 --> 00:58:08,611
like you're calling me a liar,
mi negro amigo.

895
00:58:10,488 --> 00:58:13,079
Yeah, it do sound
a whole lot like that, don't it?

896
00:58:13,950 --> 00:58:16,619
But I still ain't done it yet.

897
00:58:17,703 --> 00:58:20,664
Minnie still serve food?

898
00:58:20,832 --> 00:58:23,501
- Do you consider stew food?
- Yes.

899
00:58:23,668 --> 00:58:25,252
Then we serve food.

900
00:58:25,419 --> 00:58:29,006
She still stinking up the place
with Old Quail pipe tobacco?

901
00:58:33,010 --> 00:58:35,721
Minnie doesn't smoke a pipe.

902
00:58:35,888 --> 00:58:37,932
She rolls her own.

903
00:58:38,099 --> 00:58:40,601
Red Apple Tobacco.

904
00:58:40,768 --> 00:58:44,730
But, mi negro amigo,
I think you already know this.

905
00:58:44,897 --> 00:58:47,024
Yeah, I do, Senor Bob.

906
00:58:47,191 --> 00:58:49,735
Just seeing if you do.

907
00:59:06,544 --> 00:59:08,045
Come on!

908
00:59:32,320 --> 00:59:35,534
- Fill 'er up, O.B.
- Yeah.

909
00:59:35,698 --> 00:59:37,658
Goddamn it.

910
00:59:39,452 --> 00:59:40,870
Thank you.

911
00:59:48,753 --> 00:59:52,131
Well, cut my legs off and call me Shorty.

912
00:59:52,298 --> 00:59:55,593
Is that General Sanford Smithers I see?

913
00:59:57,261 --> 00:59:59,263
You got a good eye, son.

914
00:59:59,430 --> 01:00:03,517
Well, I'll be double-dog damned!

915
01:00:03,684 --> 01:00:05,938
General Sandy
"Don't Give a Damn" Smithers?

916
01:00:08,940 --> 01:00:11,150
Captain Chris Mannix,
Mannix's Marauders.

917
01:00:11,317 --> 01:00:12,776
Erskine's boy?

918
01:00:12,944 --> 01:00:14,570
Yes, sir.

919
01:00:14,737 --> 01:00:17,781
May I sit down, sir?

920
01:00:17,949 --> 01:00:20,618
Well, according to the Yankees,
it's a free country.

921
01:00:20,785 --> 01:00:23,954
General Sandy Smithers.

922
01:00:24,121 --> 01:00:26,290
Boy...

923
01:00:26,457 --> 01:00:27,917
oh, boy,

924
01:00:28,084 --> 01:00:31,337
did my daddy talk about you!

925
01:00:31,504 --> 01:00:35,174
I heard you gave those Blue Bellies
sweet hell.

926
01:00:36,968 --> 01:00:39,011
Me and my boys did our part.

927
01:00:39,178 --> 01:00:41,513
Just like Erskine and his boys
did their part.

928
01:00:41,681 --> 01:00:43,432
Hell yeah, we did.

929
01:00:43,599 --> 01:00:45,601
Yankee sons of bitches.

930
01:00:45,768 --> 01:00:49,063
I never knew your father, son.

931
01:00:49,230 --> 01:00:53,651
But I always respected his resolve.

932
01:00:53,818 --> 01:00:55,819
Well, thank you for saying that, General.

933
01:00:55,987 --> 01:00:58,698
Your respect would have meant
the world to him.

934
01:01:00,366 --> 01:01:03,077
Can I get you some coffee?

935
01:01:03,244 --> 01:01:04,828
That'd be nice.

936
01:01:04,996 --> 01:01:07,039
Well, how about a blanket?

937
01:01:08,582 --> 01:01:10,459
That'd be even nicer.

938
01:01:10,626 --> 01:01:13,337
Hell, you know what?
You can have mine.

939
01:01:16,716 --> 01:01:18,718
Here we go, General.

940
01:01:20,344 --> 01:01:23,389
So what brings you
out Wyoming way, sir?

941
01:01:23,556 --> 01:01:25,349
If you don't mind my askin'.

942
01:01:25,516 --> 01:01:27,267
My boy.

943
01:01:27,435 --> 01:01:31,022
- You got a boy that lives in Red Rock?
- My son.

944
01:01:32,106 --> 01:01:34,525
Chester Charles Smithers.

945
01:01:34,692 --> 01:01:38,028
He died out here a few years back.

946
01:01:38,195 --> 01:01:40,239
Forgive me, sir.

947
01:01:40,406 --> 01:01:42,700
There's no forgiveness needed, son.

948
01:01:44,035 --> 01:01:47,162
Like I said, it was a few years back.

949
01:01:47,329 --> 01:01:49,999
It was after he'd served his service.

950
01:01:52,043 --> 01:01:56,296
He came out here
to the hills of Wyoming...

951
01:01:56,464 --> 01:01:58,257
to make his fortune.

952
01:01:59,717 --> 01:02:03,095
Never to be heard from again.

953
01:02:08,559 --> 01:02:12,563
I bought him a symbolic plot...

954
01:02:12,730 --> 01:02:15,941
in the Red Rock cemetery.

955
01:02:16,108 --> 01:02:20,404
And I'm here to advise a stone maker
on his headstone.

956
01:02:20,571 --> 01:02:22,948
Was he a goner for sure?

957
01:02:23,115 --> 01:02:26,622
No chance he could be livin' the cold life
out in the woods?

958
01:02:26,786 --> 01:02:29,538
It's a rough life, but folks can learn it.

959
01:02:29,705 --> 01:02:33,083
If he'd have done
what he came out here to do,

960
01:02:33,250 --> 01:02:35,544
he'd have come home.

961
01:02:37,296 --> 01:02:39,715
Hold it. Close it, close it!

962
01:02:42,968 --> 01:02:45,721
You have to hold it closed
while I nail it shut.

963
01:02:45,888 --> 01:02:48,099
Well, who's the idiot
broke the damn door?

964
01:02:49,809 --> 01:02:52,144
just fucking hold it closed!

965
01:02:53,395 --> 01:02:55,523
Orale, cabron!

966
01:02:57,817 --> 01:03:00,152
Hold it closed.

967
01:03:00,319 --> 01:03:01,820
Okay.

968
01:03:01,987 --> 01:03:03,572
One more.

969
01:03:06,617 --> 01:03:09,328
Keep holding, keep holding,

970
01:03:09,495 --> 01:03:11,372
my negro amigo.

971
01:03:13,624 --> 01:03:16,502
We need two pieces of wood.

972
01:03:19,255 --> 01:03:21,465
Orale, cabron! All right.

973
01:03:21,632 --> 01:03:24,093
There you go, motherfucker!

974
01:03:27,805 --> 01:03:30,015
Lot of hats, Senor Bob.

975
01:03:31,767 --> 01:03:35,733
Considering Minnie's "no hats indoors" policy,
which, if I remember correctly,

976
01:03:35,896 --> 01:03:37,773
was one of them Bar of Iron rules.

977
01:03:37,940 --> 01:03:40,484
Kind of rule she'd want kept up
in her absence.

978
01:03:40,651 --> 01:03:44,492
You seem to have a laissez-faire attitude
when it come to the hats.

979
01:03:44,655 --> 01:03:45,989
I'm guilty.

980
01:03:46,157 --> 01:03:48,784
I have a laissez-faire attitude
about the hats.

981
01:03:48,951 --> 01:03:51,328
How about we forget about the hats today

982
01:03:51,495 --> 01:03:54,248
considering there is
a blizzard going on and on?

983
01:03:54,415 --> 01:03:56,792
We'll make tomorrow "No Hat Day"!

984
01:04:04,258 --> 01:04:06,718
- A large black dog.
- Now take my tip

985
01:04:06,886 --> 01:04:08,512
<i>Before you ship to join</i>

986
01:04:08,679 --> 01:04:10,889
- His name was Henry, I believe.
<i>- The iron gang</i>

987
01:04:11,056 --> 01:04:12,891
- Labrador.
<i>- Don't be too gay</i>

988
01:04:13,058 --> 01:04:14,560
<i>In Botany Bay</i>

989
01:04:14,727 --> 01:04:18,522
<i>Or else you'll surely hang</i>

990
01:04:18,689 --> 01:04:20,816
<i>Or else you'll hang,
you'll hang, said he...</i>

991
01:04:20,983 --> 01:04:22,568
You know, my daddy...

992
01:04:22,735 --> 01:04:24,319
I-I said that my-my daddy

993
01:04:24,486 --> 01:04:26,071
- always said that Davis
- A plum tree.

994
01:04:26,238 --> 01:04:27,739
was a courageous man,

995
01:04:27,907 --> 01:04:29,533
but he should've put the capital

996
01:04:29,700 --> 01:04:33,162
in Montgomery and not Richmond.

997
01:04:33,329 --> 01:04:35,581
Yes, sir. I agree with that.

998
01:04:35,748 --> 01:04:38,258
The army in northern Virginia
would've been used in a very different way.

999
01:04:38,425 --> 01:04:42,174
I said the army of north Virginia
would've been used in a very different way!

1000
01:04:42,338 --> 01:04:45,257
<i>They'll flog the poaching out of you</i>

1001
01:04:45,424 --> 01:04:47,593
<i>Out there in Botany Bay.</i>

1002
01:04:47,760 --> 01:04:49,637
Shut up!

1003
01:04:55,601 --> 01:04:57,561
O.B.

1004
01:04:59,855 --> 01:05:02,566
Do you know that nigger, sir?

1005
01:05:02,733 --> 01:05:05,485
I don't know that nigger.

1006
01:05:05,653 --> 01:05:10,074
But I know he's a nigger,
and that's all I need to know.

1007
01:05:18,958 --> 01:05:20,375
Well...

1008
01:05:20,542 --> 01:05:22,586
that nigger just ain't any nigger.

