<i>When I get to Mexico.</i>

1520
01:42:06,746 --> 01:42:09,207
Give me that guitar.

1521
01:42:11,751 --> 01:42:14,343
- Music time's over!
- Wha... Hey!

1522
01:42:17,340 --> 01:42:19,301
Turn around!

1523
01:42:26,641 --> 01:42:28,101
John, no!

1524
01:42:28,268 --> 01:42:29,727
- No, no, no, no, no!
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah!

1525
01:42:29,895 --> 01:42:32,230
Shut up!

1526
01:44:15,584 --> 01:44:19,128
When you get to hell, John,

1527
01:44:19,296 --> 01:44:21,256
tell 'em Daisy sent ya.

1528
01:44:34,603 --> 01:44:38,064
Mannix, the coffee!

1529
01:45:31,493 --> 01:45:33,411
My God!

1530
01:45:37,332 --> 01:45:39,002
Give me that fucking gun.

1531
01:45:39,959 --> 01:45:42,128
Don't test me, bitch.

1532
01:45:45,423 --> 01:45:46,799
Everybody!

1533
01:45:46,966 --> 01:45:48,509
Get your backsides up

1534
01:45:48,677 --> 01:45:50,511
against that back wall over yonder.

1535
01:45:50,679 --> 01:45:53,139
Well, goddamn it!

1536
01:45:53,306 --> 01:45:55,141
Get or don't get, Joe Gage.

1537
01:45:55,308 --> 01:45:56,643
It's up to you.

1538
01:45:56,810 --> 01:45:58,978
- I'm gettin'.
- Then get!

1539
01:46:11,324 --> 01:46:13,284
You, too, Senor Bob.

1540
01:46:18,331 --> 01:46:21,882
Everybody turn around
and put your hands on that wall.

1541
01:46:25,964 --> 01:46:28,049
Move them damn snowshoes!

1542
01:46:49,237 --> 01:46:51,072
Everybody keep your mouths shut.

1543
01:46:51,239 --> 01:46:52,782
Do like I say.

1544
01:46:52,949 --> 01:46:54,659
You open your mouth,

1545
01:46:54,826 --> 01:46:56,786
you gonna get a bullet.

1546
01:46:56,953 --> 01:46:59,628
Move a little sudden, a little strange,

1547
01:46:59,789 --> 01:47:01,958
you gonna get a bullet.

1548
01:47:02,125 --> 01:47:04,335
Not a warnin', not a question.

1549
01:47:04,502 --> 01:47:06,170
A bullet.

1550
01:47:06,337 --> 01:47:08,631
You got that?

1551
01:47:08,798 --> 01:47:10,174
Let me hear you say, "I got it!"

1552
01:47:10,341 --> 01:47:11,592
- I got it.
- I got it.

1553
01:47:11,760 --> 01:47:14,643
- I got it.
- We have it.

1554
01:47:16,139 --> 01:47:18,309
Chris Mannix,
come over here on this side.

1555
01:47:19,768 --> 01:47:21,144
Come on.

1556
01:47:26,399 --> 01:47:28,359
Take this gun out my holster.

1557
01:47:39,329 --> 01:47:41,164
Point it at them.

1558
01:47:42,582 --> 01:47:44,459
Now, like I said,

1559
01:47:44,626 --> 01:47:47,336
anybody does anything,

1560
01:47:47,504 --> 01:47:49,756
and I mean anything,

1561
01:47:49,923 --> 01:47:51,633
you kill 'em.

1562
01:47:55,428 --> 01:47:57,138
So...

1563
01:47:57,305 --> 01:48:01,357
you finally decided I'm tellin' the truth
about bein' the sheriff of Red Rock?

1564
01:48:03,019 --> 01:48:05,146
I don't know about all that.

1565
01:48:05,313 --> 01:48:07,732
But I know you ain't the killer
poisoned that coffee,

1566
01:48:07,899 --> 01:48:10,359
'cause you almost drunk it
your own damn self.

1567
01:48:10,527 --> 01:48:12,111
One of them is.

1568
01:48:20,745 --> 01:48:23,540
Give me the key.
Give me the key!

1569
01:48:35,510 --> 01:48:39,263
You motherfucking black bastard!

1570
01:48:39,430 --> 01:48:41,516
You're gonna die on this mountain,

1571
01:48:41,683 --> 01:48:44,102
and I'm gonna fucking laugh when you do!

1572
01:48:45,895 --> 01:48:48,696
- What'd I say 'bout talkin'?
- Bastard.

1573
01:48:48,857 --> 01:48:51,234
Meant it, didn't I?

1574
01:48:52,402 --> 01:48:56,203
And you need to understand
you just killed the only man here

1575
01:48:56,364 --> 01:48:59,492
committed to gettin' you to Red Rock alive.

1576
01:49:05,290 --> 01:49:07,291
Now, one of y'all...

1577
01:49:07,458 --> 01:49:10,378
is workin' with her.

1578
01:49:10,545 --> 01:49:12,547
Or two of y'all is workin' with her.

1579
01:49:12,714 --> 01:49:15,341
Or all y'all is.

1580
01:49:17,969 --> 01:49:19,804
But only one of you

1581
01:49:19,971 --> 01:49:21,515
poisoned the coffee.

1582
01:49:25,184 --> 01:49:27,812
Now, what charms this bitch got

1583
01:49:27,979 --> 01:49:30,606
make a man brave a blizzard,

1584
01:49:30,773 --> 01:49:32,609
kill in cold blood?

1585
01:49:34,444 --> 01:49:36,446
I'm sure I don't know.

1586
01:49:40,325 --> 01:49:43,619
But John Ruth's
tryin' to hang your woman.

1587
01:49:43,786 --> 01:49:45,538
So you kill him.

1588
01:49:45,705 --> 01:49:47,456
Okay.

1589
01:49:47,624 --> 01:49:49,584
Maybe.

1590
01:49:49,751 --> 01:49:52,837
But O.B. wasn't hangin' nobody.

1591
01:49:53,004 --> 01:49:54,338
He damn sure wasn't.

1592
01:49:54,505 --> 01:49:57,181
But he sure enough layin' over there
dead now, though, ain't he?

1593
01:49:57,342 --> 01:49:59,385
He damn sure is, you sons of bitches.

1594
01:49:59,552 --> 01:50:02,263
Just like any one of us
would've drunk that coffee.

1595
01:50:02,430 --> 01:50:04,473
Like me, goddamn it.

1596
01:50:04,641 --> 01:50:07,560
Now, those of y'all
with your hands on the wall

1597
01:50:07,727 --> 01:50:10,778
don't practice in poison
need to think about that.

1598
01:50:12,440 --> 01:50:16,826
Think about how it could've been you
rollin' around here on this floor.

1599
01:50:16,986 --> 01:50:20,996
And how the man standin' next to you
would be responsible.

1600
01:50:21,157 --> 01:50:23,576
And I know who I got my money on.

1601
01:50:23,743 --> 01:50:26,037
That's right, Joe Gage.

1602
01:50:26,204 --> 01:50:27,748
I'm lookin' at you.

1603
01:50:29,582 --> 01:50:31,918
Not so fast, Chris.

1604
01:50:32,085 --> 01:50:34,211
We'll get there.

1605
01:50:34,379 --> 01:50:37,340
Let's slow it down.

1606
01:50:37,507 --> 01:50:39,926
Let's slow it way down.

1607
01:50:45,473 --> 01:50:47,183
Who made the coffee?

1608
01:50:47,350 --> 01:50:48,935
He did.

1609
01:50:50,979 --> 01:50:55,573
- Yeah, he did, didn't he?
- Yeah, he did, didn't he?

1610
01:50:55,733 --> 01:50:58,945
But it's the stew that's got me thinkin'.

1611
01:51:00,363 --> 01:51:03,240
Now, how long you said
Minnie been gone?

1612
01:51:03,408 --> 01:51:04,993
A week?

1613
01:51:06,119 --> 01:51:07,578
Si.

1614
01:51:08,663 --> 01:51:10,247
See...

1615
01:51:10,415 --> 01:51:13,334
my mama used to make stew,

1616
01:51:13,501 --> 01:51:15,378
and it always tasted the same,

1617
01:51:15,545 --> 01:51:17,004
no matter the meat.

1618
01:51:17,171 --> 01:51:20,681
And there was another fellow
on the plantation, Uncle Charly.

1619
01:51:20,842 --> 01:51:22,343
He made stew, too.

1620
01:51:22,510 --> 01:51:24,136
And like my mama,

1621
01:51:24,303 --> 01:51:28,140
I ate his stew
from the time I was a whipper

1622
01:51:28,307 --> 01:51:30,685
till I was a full-grown man.

1623
01:51:31,894 --> 01:51:33,771
No matter the meat,

1624
01:51:33,938 --> 01:51:36,774
it always tasted like Uncle Charly's stew.

1625
01:51:38,067 --> 01:51:41,660
Now, I ain't had Minnie's stew
in six months, so I ain't no expert.

1626
01:51:41,821 --> 01:51:45,866
But that damn sure is...

1627
01:51:46,034 --> 01:51:48,661
Minnie's stew.

1628
01:51:48,828 --> 01:51:51,122
So if Minnie is on the north side

1629
01:51:51,289 --> 01:51:53,749
visitin' her mama for a week,

1630
01:51:53,916 --> 01:51:56,753
how'd she make the stew this mornin'?

1631
01:52:01,049 --> 01:52:03,884
And this...

1632
01:52:04,052 --> 01:52:07,805
this is Sweet Dave's chair.

1633
01:52:07,972 --> 01:52:09,974
When I sat in it earlier,

1634
01:52:10,141 --> 01:52:11,892
I couldn't believe it.

1635
01:52:12,060 --> 01:52:14,520
Nobody sits in Sweet Dave's chair.

1636
01:52:14,687 --> 01:52:16,897
This may be Minnie's place,

1637
01:52:17,065 --> 01:52:20,276
but this is damn sure

1638
01:52:20,443 --> 01:52:22,528
Sweet Dave's chair.

1639
01:52:24,864 --> 01:52:28,034
And if he went to the north side...

1640
01:52:29,786 --> 01:52:31,954
...I'm pretty goddamn sure

1641
01:52:32,121 --> 01:52:34,832
this chair be goin' with him.

1642
01:52:39,462 --> 01:52:41,255
What's in the chair?

1643
01:52:41,422 --> 01:52:43,549
Just what I thought.

1644
01:52:43,716 --> 01:52:46,677
Sweet Dave's goddamn blood.

1645
01:52:52,433 --> 01:52:56,729
So, are you actually
accusing me of murder?

1646
01:52:59,941 --> 01:53:02,860
Way I see it, Senor Bob,

1647
01:53:03,027 --> 01:53:06,113
is whoever is workin' with her

1648
01:53:06,280 --> 01:53:09,075
ain't who they say they is.

1649
01:53:09,242 --> 01:53:11,035
And if it's you,

1650
01:53:11,202 --> 01:53:13,287
that means Minnie and her man

1651
01:53:13,454 --> 01:53:15,247
ain't at her mama's.

1652
01:53:15,414 --> 01:53:18,834
They layin' out back there
dead somewhere.

1653
01:53:19,001 --> 01:53:21,003
Or if it's you, little British man,

1654
01:53:21,170 --> 01:53:24,340
the real Oswaldo Mobray
layin' in a ditch somewhere

1655
01:53:24,507 --> 01:53:26,967
and you just a English fella
passin' off his papers.

1656
01:53:27,135 --> 01:53:29,845
Or we go by my theory,

1657
01:53:30,012 --> 01:53:32,890
which is the ugliest guy did it.

1658
01:53:33,057 --> 01:53:35,559
Which makes it you, Joe Gage.

1659
01:53:35,726 --> 01:53:39,980
So I take it
you deduced the coffee was poisoned

1660
01:53:40,148 --> 01:53:42,108
while you were murdering the old man?

1661
01:53:43,276 --> 01:53:44,902
Yes.

1662
01:53:45,069 --> 01:53:47,530
Well, mi negro amigo,

1663
01:53:47,697 --> 01:53:49,824
during that whole incident,

1664
01:53:49,991 --> 01:53:52,535
I was sitting on that side of the room

1665
01:53:52,702 --> 01:53:54,870
playing "Silent Night" on the piano.

1666
01:53:55,037 --> 01:53:57,998
I ain't say you poisoned the coffee.

1667
01:53:58,166 --> 01:54:01,127
I said you didn't make the stew.

1668
01:54:02,670 --> 01:54:06,090
My theory is...

1669
01:54:06,257 --> 01:54:09,218
you workin' with the man

1670
01:54:09,385 --> 01:54:11,011
who poisoned the coffee,

1671
01:54:11,179 --> 01:54:13,514
and both of y'all murdered Minnie,

1672
01:54:13,681 --> 01:54:16,559
Sweet Dave and whoever else
picked this bad-luck day

1673
01:54:16,726 --> 01:54:19,520
to visit Minnie's Haberdashery
this mornin'.

1674
01:54:19,687 --> 01:54:23,399
And at some point, y'all intended

1675
01:54:23,566 --> 01:54:26,026
to bushwhack John Ruth

1676
01:54:26,194 --> 01:54:28,904
and free Daisy.

1677
01:54:29,071 --> 01:54:31,448
But you didn't count on the blizzard,

1678
01:54:31,616 --> 01:54:34,660
and you didn't count on the two of us.

1679
01:54:39,332 --> 01:54:41,292
That's far as I got. How am I doing?

1680
01:54:45,213 --> 01:54:47,631
You're a real imaginative nigger,

1681
01:54:47,798 --> 01:54:49,967
ain't you?

1682
01:54:50,134 --> 01:54:52,928
So, do you intend to murder me

1683
01:54:53,095 --> 01:54:55,389
based on a far-fetched nigger theory,

1684
01:54:55,556 --> 01:54:57,934
or can you prove it, cabron?

1685
01:54:59,477 --> 01:55:04,565
It ain't so far-fetched, Senor Bob.

1686
01:55:04,732 --> 01:55:07,485
And it's a little bit more than a theory.

1687
01:55:11,864 --> 01:55:14,366
How long you say
you been workin' for Minnie?

1688
01:55:14,533 --> 01:55:16,285
Four months.

1689
01:55:18,246 --> 01:55:20,873
See, if you'd have been here
two and a half years ago,

1690
01:55:21,040 --> 01:55:24,835
you'd know 'bout that sign
used to hang up over the bar.

1691
01:55:25,002 --> 01:55:27,463
Minnie mention that to you?

1692
01:55:28,756 --> 01:55:30,591
No.

1693
01:55:30,758 --> 01:55:33,552
You want to know
what that sign said, Senor Bob?

1694
01:55:35,680 --> 01:55:39,976
"No dogs or Mexicans allowed."

1695
01:55:43,479 --> 01:55:47,031
Now, Minnie hung that sign up
the day she opened this haberdashery.

1696
01:55:47,191 --> 01:55:50,110
And it hung over that bar every day

1697
01:55:50,278 --> 01:55:53,239
till she took it down
a little over two years ago.

1698
01:55:54,865 --> 01:55:56,617
You know why she took it down?

1699
01:55:58,494 --> 01:56:00,997
She started lettin' in dogs.

1700
01:56:04,709 --> 01:56:08,629
Now, Minnie liked just about everybody,

1701
01:56:08,796 --> 01:56:10,881
but she sure don't

1702
01:56:11,048 --> 01:56:12,841
like Mexicans.

1703
01:56:13,009 --> 01:56:14,885
So when you tell me

1704
01:56:15,052 --> 01:56:18,555
Minnie went to the north side
to visit her mama,

1705
01:56:18,723 --> 01:56:21,267
well, I find that highly unlikely.

1706
01:56:21,434 --> 01:56:24,645
But okay, maybe.

1707
01:56:24,812 --> 01:56:27,356
But when you tell me

1708
01:56:27,523 --> 01:56:31,151
Minnie Mink took the haberdashery,

1709
01:56:31,319 --> 01:56:35,197
the most precious thing to her
in the whole world,

1710
01:56:35,364 --> 01:56:39,327
and left it in the hands
of a goddamn Mexican?

1711
01:56:40,828 --> 01:56:45,297
Well, that's what I meant in the barn when
I said that sure don't sound like Minnie.

1712
01:56:47,376 --> 01:56:50,337
Now I am calling you a liar,

1713
01:56:50,504 --> 01:56:52,465
Senor Bob.

1714
01:56:53,716 --> 01:56:55,676
And if you lyin',

1715
01:56:55,843 --> 01:56:57,345
which you are...

1716
01:56:58,971 --> 01:57:01,981
...then you killed Minnie.
And Sweet Dave.

1717
01:57:20,409 --> 01:57:22,786
Four measly bullets,

1718
01:57:22,953 --> 01:57:26,040
and there goes Senor Bob.

1719
01:57:27,708 --> 01:57:30,961
But that still don't get us no closer

1720
01:57:31,128 --> 01:57:34,465
to which one of y'all
poisoned the coffee, though.

1721
01:57:34,632 --> 01:57:37,766
- Do it, Chris?
- No, it sure don't.

1722
01:57:43,808 --> 01:57:47,610
Now, one of y'all poisoned this coffee
to free Daisy.

1723
01:57:47,770 --> 01:57:49,396
If I don't hear a confession

1724
01:57:49,563 --> 01:57:52,649
from one of you motherfuckers
quick, fast and in a hurry,

1725
01:57:52,817 --> 01:57:55,319
I'm gonna pour this whole pot of coffee

1726
01:57:55,486 --> 01:57:58,114
down that bitch's goddamn throat.

1727
01:57:59,407 --> 01:58:02,534
Okay. Time's up.

1728
01:58:02,701 --> 01:58:03,952
Stop!

1729
01:58:04,120 --> 01:58:05,954
All right, I did it.

1730
01:58:06,122 --> 01:58:08,040
It was me. I poisoned the coffee.

1731
01:58:09,166 --> 01:58:12,128
I fuckin' knew it!

1732
01:58:13,838 --> 01:58:16,173
You gonna die now,
you murderin' bastard!

1733
01:58:16,340 --> 01:58:19,343
Major Warren,
please let me send this ugly

1734
01:58:19,510 --> 01:58:21,345
son of a bitch to hell.

1735
01:58:21,512 --> 01:58:23,263
You killed O.B.

1736
01:58:23,431 --> 01:58:26,774
He was worth ten of you.
Warren, can I kill him?

1737
01:58:26,934 --> 01:58:28,606
Say adios to your huevos.

1738
01:58:35,651 --> 01:58:38,404
Major Warren!

1739
01:58:55,546 --> 01:58:58,715
I ain't got no gun,

1740
01:58:58,883 --> 01:59:01,343
Sheriff.

1741
01:59:35,920 --> 01:59:37,254
Roy!

1742
01:59:37,421 --> 01:59:39,006
Good boy.

1743
01:59:42,885 --> 01:59:44,386
Get up!

1744
01:59:44,553 --> 01:59:46,854
Get up there! Get up!

1745
01:59:47,014 --> 01:59:49,600
Packer, Roy, get up!

1746
01:59:49,767 --> 01:59:51,351
Get up!

1747
01:59:51,519 --> 01:59:54,028
Get up there! Get up!
Get up!

1748
01:59:54,188 --> 01:59:57,072
Get up there! Get up!
Get up!

1749
01:59:57,233 --> 01:59:58,568
Go!

1750
02:00:00,778 --> 02:00:04,156
Go! Go! Go!

1751
02:00:04,323 --> 02:00:06,659
Go! Go!

1752
02:00:08,786 --> 02:00:10,120
Go!

1753
02:01:11,181 --> 02:01:12,683
Get up. Get up.

1754
02:01:12,850 --> 02:01:14,935
- Get up! Get up!
- Get up!

1755
02:01:15,102 --> 02:01:17,862
Get up! Get up!

1756
02:01:26,530 --> 02:01:30,291
Get up! Get up!

1757
02:01:33,954 --> 02:01:35,539
Get up! Get up!

1758
02:01:51,805 --> 02:01:53,140
Easy.

1759
02:01:54,475 --> 02:01:56,351
Hey, Charly, my boy.

1760
02:01:56,518 --> 02:01:59,069
- How the hell are you?
- Hiya, Ed. Hiya, Judy.

1761
02:01:59,229 --> 02:02:00,606
Yeah!

1762
02:02:02,941 --> 02:02:05,201
- How many you got?
- Full house today, friend.

1763
02:02:05,361 --> 02:02:08,287
- Got one in there waitin'.
- Well, he's gonna have to keep on waitin'.

1764
02:02:08,447 --> 02:02:10,873
- We ain't got no room.
- Well, you need to tell Minnie.

1765
02:02:11,033 --> 02:02:13,918
'Cause he been here two days,
and Minnie wants him out of here.

1766
02:02:14,078 --> 02:02:15,912
Well, I can't give him a seat I don't have.

1767
02:02:16,080 --> 02:02:18,540
Listen, why don't you
take the passengers inside

1768
02:02:18,707 --> 02:02:21,509
and introduce 'em to Minnie,
warm yourself up and drink some coffee.

1769
02:02:21,669 --> 02:02:23,005
Yeah.

1770
02:02:28,302 --> 02:02:31,143
Here we are, everybody.
Minnie's Haberdashery.

1771
02:02:31,303 --> 02:02:33,771
Step outside, you and your friends
can stretch your legs.

1772
02:02:33,931 --> 02:02:37,525
When you're ready, step on inside,
get warm by the fire, get some coffee in you.

1773
